<HEAD><TITLE>Phd-projects Enschede 1996</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Department of Separation Technology, Textile Technology Group<HR></H2>

<TT><PRE>
University of Twente
Faculty of Chemical Technology
P.O. Box 217
NL 7500 AE Enschede

telephone: +31 (0)53 489 2920/3696
fax:       +31 (0)53 489 3849
</PRE></TT>

<HR>

<B>Chair:</B>
Prof. Dr. Ir. M.M.C.G. Warmoeskerken (part time)<P>

<B>Senior Scientist:</B><BR>
It. H. Gooijer<P>

<B>Ph.D. Student:</B><BR>
C.W. den Engelsen<P>

The group is maintained by the Foundation for Structured Materials and is aimed at providing
education and performing research in the area of textile technology to support the Dutch textile
industry. The research programme is focussed on wet treatment processes of textiles. Current
research projects are:<BR>
- foam application<BR>
- flow through textiles<BR>
<P>
Projects under development are:<BR>
- application of ultrasonic waves<BR>
- enzymatic treatment processes<BR>
- modelling and simulation with help of CFD and DPD<BR>

