<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Reactor design for the enzymatic synthesis of oligosaccharides
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H1>Reactor design for the enzymatic synthesis of oligosaccharides</H1>

<B>PhD-fellow:</B> Ir. Floor Boon (tel. 0317-482240)<BR>
<B>Project term: </B>May 1995 - May 1999<BR>
<B>E-mail:</B> <A HREF="mailto:Floor.Boon@algemeen.pk.wau.nl">Floor.Boon@algemeen.pk.wau.nl</A><BR>
<B>Sponsor:</B> ABON and Borculo Whey Products<BR>

<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Introduction</B><BR>
There is a growing interest in the
synthesis of oligosaccharides for the application in 'functional
foods'. The ingestion of oligosaccharides encourages the proliferation
of <I>Bifidobacterium</I> spp. in the intestine.
<P>
The enzymatic synthesis of oligosaccharides
is possible with glycosidases. The reaction is kinetically controlled
and has to be stopped to prevent hydrolysis of the oligosaccharides.
<P>
<B>Aim</B><BR>
The main objective of this project
is to design a suitable reactor for the enzymatic synthesis of
oligosaccharides. The development of a kinetic model is necessary
to achieve this aim.
<P>
<B>Results</B><BR>
The model system chosen is the enzymatic
production of trisaccharides with the enzyme -galactosidase and
lactose as a substrate.
<P>
The kinetic model to describe the
trisaccharide synthesis and lactose hydrolysis is shown in figure
1. For -galactosidase from <I>Aspergillus oryzae</I> galactose
inhibition is included.
<P>
<IMG SRC="boon1.gif"><BR>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Figure 1.</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2>
Kinetic model for the enzymatic synthesis of trisaccharides.</FONT>
<P>
Data were obtained from experiments
at different initial lactose concentrations with the -galactosidase
from <I>Aspergillus oryzae.</I> The data were fitted with the
kinetic model shown in figure 1.
<P>
In figure 2 the best fit is shown
at one initial lactose concentration.
<P>
<IMG SRC="boon2.gif">
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Figure 2.</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2>
Conversion of lactose with -galactosidase from <I>Aspergillus
oryzae</I>. Initial lactose concentration is 0.56 mol/kg.</FONT>
<P>
For the high initial lactose concentrations
one parameter set was found. The production of trisaccharides
and hydrolysis of lactose can be well predicted with the kinetic
model of figure 1.
<P>
Further different possibilities to
increase the trisaccharide production have been studied with the
model. Calculations have shown that the trisaccharide concentration
can be increased by removal of trisaccharides, monosaccharides
and increasing of the initial lactose concentration.
<P>
<B>Future research</B><BR>
With the developed kinetic model
it will be possible to predict the synthesis of trisaccharides
in different reactor systems. A suitable reactor for the synthesis
of trisaccharides can be developed and the model will be validated.

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 01/11/96</CENTER></H6>

