<HEAD>
<TITLE>The implementation of Quantitative Risk Analysis in HACCP as a tool for the production of safe foods
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H1>The implementation of Quantitative Risk Analysis in HACCP as a tool for the production of safe foods</H1>

<B>PhD-fellow: Ir. Suzanne van Gerwen</B><BR>
<B>Sponsor: Wageningen Agricultural University</B><BR>

<HR SIZE=0>

<FONT COLOR=#0000FF>Introduction</FONT><BR>
The Hazard Analysis Critical Control Point (HACCP) system is mainly
used in a qualitative manner. The aim of this project is the realization
of a quantitative approach of this system. This will be done by
implementation of Quantitative Risk Analysis (<B>QRA</B>) for
food products in the existing HACCP system.<BR>
<P>
<FONT COLOR=#0000FF>Methods</FONT><BR>
In the development of QRA an objective
method will be made for:<BR>
1. identification of hazards,<BR>
2. estimation of the average amount of pathogens<BR>
3. estimation of the probability of presence of pathogens<BR>
4. conduction of a failure analysis.<BR>
<P>
<IMG SRC="gerwen1.gif">
<P>
figure 1. Combination of objective method with dose-response data
<P>
As shown in figure 1 combination of the method with dose-response
data will result in QRA. <BR>
<P>
<IMG SRC="gerwen2.gif"><BR>
<P>
figure 2. Decision tree for determination of microbiological hazards
<P>
<FONT COLOR=#0000FF>Results</FONT><BR>
A decision tree (figure 2) has been established by which the mentioned
objective method in QRA can be established.<BR>
<P>
For a good estimate of the hazards in food products and the control
of hazards the decision tree will be consulted at least twice.
Firstly to roughly estimate the main hazards and secondly to perform
a more detailed hazard analysis to find less obvious hazards.
<P>
The quantitative HACCP system is being implemented into a computer
program to make it easy accessible for users.<BR>
<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 01/11/96</CENTER></H6>

