<TD>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Process Design Study Tour 1996<BR>
Picture book (an impression)</H2>

<H6 ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="../../pic/city/bl_a.gif" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=12 WIDTH=14>UVA
<IMG SRC="../../pic/city/or_d.gif" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=12 WIDTH=14>TUD <IMG SRC="../../pic/city/or_e.gif" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=12 WIDTH=14>TUE
<IMG SRC="../../pic/city/or_t.gif" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=12 WIDTH=14>UT <IMG SRC="../../pic/city/bl_g.gif" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=12 WIDTH=14>RUG
<IMG SRC="../../pic/city/bl_w.gif" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=12 WIDTH=14>LUW </H6>
</TD>

<TD><MAP NAME="logo.map"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="38,21,108,51" HREF="../../index.html"></MAP><IMG USEMAP="#logo.map" SRC="../../pic/logo/det__agw.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=85 WIDTH=149>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="sspt.gif" WIDTH=109 HEIGHT=85 ALT="SSPT"></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<HR>

<H3><A HREF="monday.html">Monday</A>:</H3>
We visited <A HREF="http://www.huels.de/">H&uuml;ls</A> <A HREF="huls.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_huls.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Huls" ALIGN=CENTER></A>.

In spite of the collision of two of our busses everybody <A HREF="restaurant1.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_restaurant1.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Diner" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="restaurant2.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_restaurant2.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Diner" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="restaurant3.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_restaurant3.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Diner" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="restaurant4.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_restaurant4.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Diner" ALIGN=CENTER></A> enjoys the diner at the restaurant in Koblenz.

<H3><A HREF="tuesday.html">Tuesday</A>:</H3>
We went to <A HREF="http://www.basf-ag.basf.de/basf/html/d/home.htm">BASF</A>.

At the end of this day BASF surprised us (thanks!) with a visit to a beautiful castle <A HREF="heidelberg1.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_heidelberg1.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Castle" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="heidelberg2.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_heidelberg2.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Castle" ALIGN=CENTER></A> in Heidelberg.

Inside the castle we walked over the largest wine vessel <A HREF="wijn.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_wijn.jpg" WIDTH=33 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Vessel" ALIGN=CENTER></A> of the world (about 240.000 litres!).

After visiting the castle we met a lot of (about 11) BASF employees during a great diner <A HREF="basf1.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_basf1.jpg" WIDTH=33 HEIGHT=50 ALT="BASF" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="basf2.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_basf2.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="BASF" ALIGN=CENTER></A> at a beautiful restaurant in Heidelberg.

<H3><A HREF="wednesday.html">Wednesday</A>:</H3>

We had some interesting discussions at the <A HREF="http://www.anorg.chemie.uni-stuttgart.de/">University of Stuttgart</A>.

Around midnight some of us <A HREF="piano1.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_piano1.jpg" WIDTH=33 HEIGHT=50 ALT="BASF" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="piano2.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_piano2.jpg" WIDTH=33 HEIGHT=50 ALT="BASF" ALIGN=CENTER></A> proved to be musical talents.

When the barman wanted to close some of us <A HREF="bar.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_bar.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="BASF" ALIGN=CENTER></A> didn't agree.

<H3><A HREF="thursday.html">Thursday</A>:</H3>
We first visited the <A HREF="http://neon.coe.fr/">council of Europe</A> <A HREF="zaal.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_zaal.jpg" WIDTH=124 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Council" ALIGN=CENTER></A> in Strasbourg,

and in the afternoon we went to Nancy <A HREF="nancy1.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_nancy1.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Nancy" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="nancy2.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_nancy2.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Nancy" ALIGN=CENTER></A> to

see how <A HREF="../../../~pk/swaaij.html">professor van Swaaij</A> <A HREF="swaaij1.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_swaaij1.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Swaaij" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="swaaij2.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_swaaij2.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Swaaij" ALIGN=CENTER></A> received a doctorate of honour.

<H3><A HREF="friday.html">Friday</A>:</H3>
In the morning we visited a site of <A HREF="http://www.solvay.com/">Solvay</A> and in the afternoon we visited the <A HREF="http://www.ensic.u-nancy.fr/">ENSIC</A> in Nancy.

In the evening we played the popular french game "Pétanque" <A HREF="jdb.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_jdb.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="JdB" ALIGN=CENTER></A> with some people from the ENSIC.

By using his tie <A HREF="frank.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_frank.jpg" WIDTH=33 HEIGHT=49 ALT="Frank" ALIGN=CENTER></A> to measure the distance between the balls, Frank den Hartog shows that he's very smart.

After the game we ate a piza <A HREF="piza1.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_piza1.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Piza" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="piza2.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_piza2.jpg" WIDTH=33 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Piza" ALIGN=CENTER></A> in Nancy.

<H3><A HREF="saterday.html">Saterday</A>:</H3>
We had a lunch <A HREF="remouchamps1.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_remouchamps1.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Lunch" ALIGN=CENTER></A> <A HREF="remouchamps2.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_remouchamps2.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Lunch" ALIGN=CENTER></A> in Remouchamps. 

Later it was time to say goodbye <A HREF="asselbergs.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_asselbergs.jpg" WIDTH=33 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Carel" ALIGN=CENTER></A> with some presents <A HREF="paraplu.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_paraplu.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Umbrella" ALIGN=CENTER></A> in Remouchamps.

There we also made a picture of the committee <A HREF="commissie.jpg"><IMG SRC="tn_commissie.jpg" WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=50 ALT="Committee" ALIGN=CENTER></A> who organised the trip.

<H3><A HREF="dsm.html">DSM excursion</A>:</H3>
At the end of October we had an excursion of two days to our sponsor <A HREF="http://www.dsm.nl/">DSM</A>.

<P>

<H5 ALIGN=CENTER>[ <A HREF="index.html">Index</A> - <A HREF="doel.html">Achtergrond</A> - <A HREF="deelnemers.html">Deelnemers</A> - Photos - <A HREF="monday.html">Monday</A> - <A HREF="tuesday.html">Tuesday</A> - <A HREF="wednesday.html">Wednesday</A> - <A HREF="thursday.html">Thursday</A> - <A HREF="friday.html">Friday</A> - <A HREF="saterday.html">Saterday</A> - <A HREF="dsm.html">DSM</A> ]</H5>

