<H3>Faculty of Chemistry</H3>

<H4>Department of Chemical Engineering</H4>

<UL>
<P><B><A HREF="crex_000.html">Chemical Reaction Engineering</A> (prof.dr.
R. Krishna)</B>
<LI><A HREF="cr1.html">A unified approach to ...</A> </LI>
<LI><A HREF="cr2.html">Unified approach to scale up of &quot;fluidized&quot;
multiphase reactors</A> </LI>
<LI><A HREF="cr3.html">Gas holdup</A> </LI>
<LI><A HREF="cr4.html">Holdups in slurry bubble columns</A> </LI>
<LI><A HREF="cr5.html">Generalized model</A> </LI>
<LI><A HREF="cr6.html">Synthesis of &quot;ideal&quot; reactor and separator
configurations</A> </LI>
</UL>

<UL>
<P><B><A HREF="cpcx_000.html">Chemical Processes and Catalysis</A> (prof.dr.ir.
A. Bliek)</B>
<LI><A HREF="alfred.html">Microwave heating of solid catalysts</A> (A.
Bliek) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="sjoerd.html">Selective catalytic reduction (SCR) of NO with
NH<SUB>3</SUB> over MnO<SUB>x</SUB>/Al<SUB>2</SUB>O<SUB>3</SUB> catalysts
at low temperatures</A> (W.S. Kijlstra) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="frank.html">Forced oscillations on catalytic systems</A> (F.
van Neer) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="danny.html">The copper catalysed hydrogenolysis of fatty methyl
esters</A> (D.S. Brands) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="moniquez.html">Selection criteria for carbon supported noble
metal catalysts in three-phase reaction systems</A> (M. van der Zon) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="remko.html">New methods for the preparation of oleochemicals
using solid acid catalysts</A> (R.M. Koster) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="marjo.html">Porosity of heterogenous catalysts</A> (M.C. Mittelmeijer-Hazeleger)
</LI>
</UL>

<UL>
<P><B><A HREF="psex_000.html">Process Systems Engineering</A> (prof.dr.
P.D. Iedema, prof.dr. A.K. Smilde)</B>
<LI><A HREF="vacan1.html">Control of reactive polymer processing</A> (P.
Hamersma, H. Hoefsloot, P. Iedema) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="vacan2.html">Reactive polymer systems in a static mixer reactor</A>
(P. Hamersma, H. Hoefsloot, P. Iedema) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="age.html">Plant-wide multivariate statistical process control</A>
(A.K. Smilde, P.D. Iedema, C. Georgakis) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="marcel.html">Dynamic gas/liquid flow in pipes and regular
T-junctions</A> (M. Ottens) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="florian.html">Including external process variables in multivariate
calibration of process instruments</A> (F. Wulfert) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="hans.html">Bias by sample injection and detection in capillary
zone electrophoresis</A> (H. van der Moolen) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="michael.html">Plant wide instrumentation: combining analytical
measurements made at different locations in a process</A> (M. Muller) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="raivo1.html">Maximum information from separations</A> (R.
Kilg) </LI>
<LI><A HREF="renger.html">Optimal calibration of optical emission spectrometers
