<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Process &amp; Apparatus Development School Delft</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H3>Phase A: widening of basis knowledge<HR></H3>

During this phase the knowledge of the member of the course will be widened. The underlying idea is that five disciplines
can be indicated that play a major role in the work of a process engineer:
<UL>
<LI>applied mathematics and informatics
<LI>physical and chemical basis
<LI>technology en apparatus knowledge
<LI>social sciences
<LI>communication
</UL>

From at least three of the above disciplines a study part has to be chosen. Five key subjects are obligatory:
<UL>
<LI>chemical thermodynamics
<LI>physical technology of conversion processes and product processing
<LI>process engineering
<LI>apparatus for the process industry
<LI>process design and simulation
</UL>

A total of 480 hours is available for this part.<P>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> Process &amp; Apparatus Development School Delft

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl"> OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 29/12/95</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
