<HEAD><TITLE>Process &amp; Apparatus Development School Delft</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H3>Phase B: deepening of relevant knowledge<HR></H3>

During this phase some subjects are discussed at a more advanced level, mainly by use of courses given specifically for the development course. The subjects include:
<OL>
<LI>one exam part of each of the following disciplines (160 hours):
   <UL>
   <LI>thermodynamics
   <LI>transport phenomena
   </UL>
<LI>one exam part of at least four of the following disciplines (480 hours):
   <UL>
   <LI>conversion technology and reactor engineering
   <LI>separation processes
   <LI>apparatus aspects en material science
   <LI>process integration and -control
   <LI>special processes/processes under special conditions
   <LI>durable technology and development
   </UL>
</OL>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> Process &amp; Apparatus Development School Delft

