<HEAD><TITLE>Process &amp; Product Development School Eindhoven</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H3>First part of the course Process &amp; Product Development<HR></H3>

During the first year of the course the student will attend a lot of lectures, both in and outside Eindhoven. External courses and visits to companies are part of the training. The courses are given by  universal teachers and teachers from several companies (Akzo Nobel, Dow, DSM, Fluor Daniel).<P>

The first year of the training can be divided into three parts:
<OL>
<LI>Common basis
<LI>Obligatory courses
<LI>Differentiation and free choice
</OL>

A summary is given in <A HREF="table.html">this table</A>.<P>

During the common basis emphasis is on basis knowledge at a higher than universal level.<P>

Every student follows two large obligatory courses, Plantdesign and -operation and Common Production. These courses are teached by teachers from the industry.<P>

During the differentiation and free choice another large course or training period will be followed . Besides the student can follow some other courses of his or her choice.<P>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> Process &amp; Product Development School Eindhoven

