<HEAD><TITLE>Process &amp; Product Development School Eindhoven</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H3>Design project of the course Process &amp; Product Development<HR></H3>

Mainly during the second year of the course the students will need much time for their design project. This project must have an integrating character thanks to the co-operation of several disciplines.<P>

The project will be carried out at one or more of the faculties of the university, at a company or at a research institute. To stimulate team-work it is possible that more then one student carry out a project.<P>

Some examples of design projects are:

<UL>
<LI>Design of a catalyst and reactor for the conversion of mercaptane.
<LI>Modelation and improvement of a heater.
<LI>Design of a packed bed for application in oxidative methane-coupling.
<LI>Modelation and design of a monolith reactor for cleaning of exhaust-gases of cars.
<LI>Modelation and design of new hydrocracking-catalysts.
<LI>Design of new polymer material with perfect properties.
<LI>Modelation of a high-temperature furnace with oxidizing environment, followed by design and construction of a prototype.
<LI>Design and realization of a fluid bed granulator.
<LI>Design of a gascyclone for particle separation at high temperatures.
</UL>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> Process &amp; Product Development School Eindhoven

