<HEAD><TITLE>Process Development School Enschede</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H3>First year of the Process Development Course<HR></H3>

The period of intensive courses is divided into three parts (respectively 2, 6 and 4 months):

<UL>

<LI>a part in which <A HREF="0part.html">supplementary courses</A> are given. This part precedes the actual course and is needed to fill up the knowledge of students who did not graduate in process technology. For every candidate an individual program can be made.

<LI>a part in which existing knowledge is extended. The <A HREF="1stpart.html">courses</A> of this part are done either individual or in teams and if needed lectures are given. There is often a close contact between the student and the master or employer. These courses are often finished by a project. A total of six courses have to be done.

<LI>a part in which knowledge of different subjects is integrated during a process development and process design project: the course <A HREF="2ndpart.html">process plant design</A>.

</UL>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> Process Development School Enschede

