<H3>Symposia en congressen</H3>

<A HREF="#fondsen"><B>Fondsenwerving in het Hoger Onderwijs</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#euromembrane"><B>Euromembrane 1997, Progress in Membrane Science and Technology</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#interfaces"><B>Interfaces against Pollution</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#liquid"><B>Liquid-Liquid Two-Phase Flow and Transport Phenomena Symposium</B></A>

<P>
<A NAME="fondsen"><I>10 oktober 1996</I><BR>
<B>Fondsenwerving in het Hoger Onderwijs</B><BR>
"Money makes the brains go around", congres gehouden in het Fortis Auditorium te Utrecht.<BR>
<I>Programma:</I>
<UL>
<LI>Ontvangst
<LI>Welkomstwoord
<LI>Opening
<LI>De maatschappijlijke positie van het Hoger Onderwijs
<LI>Money makes the brains go around
<LI>Pauze
<LI>Development and fundraising in England
<LI>Forumdiscussie en gelegenheid tot het stellen van vragen
<LI>Lunch
<LI>Cases eerste sessie
<LI>Cases tweede sessie
<LI>Pauze
<LI>Het bedrijfsleven en het hoger onderwijs: een affectieve of een effectieve relatie
<LI>Afsluiting door de dagvoorzitter
<LI>Borrel
</UL>
<I>Kosten:</I><BR>
De deelnamekosten voor het congres bedraagt f 395,-- p.p. Voor studenten geldt een speciaal tarief van f 75,-- p.p. In de prijs zijn een congresmap met samenvattingen van de lezingen, een lunch en consumpties inbegrepen.<BR>
<I>Inlichtingen:</I><BR>
Voor inlichingen kunt u terecht bij Inge van Gaal, FBU-Congresbureau, Universiteit Utrecht, Postbus 80125, 3508 TC Utrecht, tel. 030 - 253 2728, fax 030 - 253 3667, e-mail <A HREF="mailto:i.vangaal@fbu.ruu.nl">i.vangaal@fbu.ruu.nl.</A>

<P>
<A NAME="euromembrane"><I>23 - 27 juni 1997</I><BR>
<B>Euromembrane 1997<BR>
Progress in Membrane Science and Technology</B><BR>
The scope of the Symposium will be "new aspects of membrane science and technology". The Symposium is directed to scientists concerned with the development and application of new membranes and membrane processes. The program for the Symposium will include invited lectures, poster sessions and oral presentations on the following topics:
<UL>
<LI>Membrane formation
<LI>Membrane characterization
<LI>Gas separation
<LI>Pervaporation
<LI>Liquid membranes
<LI>Catalytic membranes
<LI>Process design
<LI>New materials
<LI>New applications
</UL>
<I>Symposium Secretariat:</I><BR>
Convention Bureau Basics, P.O. Box 217, NL-7500 AE Enschede, tel. +31 53 4332035, fax +31 53 435 6770, e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:pmst97@basics,utwente.nl">pmst97@basics,utwente.nl</A>.

<P>
<A NAME="interfaces"><I>10 - 13 augustus 1997</I><BR>
<B>Interfaces against Pollution</B><BR>
International Papers LuW.<BR>
<I>Topics:</I>
<UL>
<LI>Colloid and interface science of particles and contaminants in the environment (particles and/or polyelectrolytes and contaminants in aquatic and soil systems).
<LI>Fundamental colloidal and interfacial aspects of monitoring, remediation and prevention (adsorption, wetting, flotation, micellization, (ad)solubilization, emulsification).
<LI>Remediation and prevention (waste immobilisation, removal of heavy metal ions or organic components, soil characteristics and remediation, recycling and reclamation).
<LI>Environmental catalysis/bio-remediation (adsorbent/catalyst preparation and characterisation, photo-catalysis near surfaces, micellar catalysis, enzymes on supports, bacterial adhesion).
</UL>
<I>Conference fees:</I>
The total conference fee covering registration, conference information, abstract book, coffee or tea and all meals (including the conference dinner) will amount to about Dfl. 600,--.<BR>
<I>Conference secretariat IAP97:</I><BR>
Fax: +31 (317) 48377, e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:IAP97@fenk.wau.nl">IAP97@fenk.wau.nl</A>, p.o. Box 8038, 6700 EK Wageningen.

<P>
<A NAME="liquid"><I>3 - 7 november 1997</I><BR>
<B>Liquid-Liquid Two-Phase Flow and Transport Phenomena</B><BR>
Symposium, Antalya, Turkey.<BR>
<I>Objective</I><BR>
The goal of the symposium is to provide a forum for the exposure and exchange of ideas, methods, and results in liquid-liquid flow heat and mass transfer.<BR>
While papers on all aspects of liquid-liquid phenomena will be welcome, contributions are especially invited on the following subjects:
<UL>
<LI>Liquid-liquid systems and applications
<LI>Modeling - flow patterns and flow characteristics
<LI>Modeling - stability and transitions
<LI>Liquid-liquid separation, phenomena and equipment
<LI>Measurement and instrumentation
<LI>Characteristics and effective properties of liquid-liquid systems
<LI>Multi-phase systems
<LI>Surface phenomena
</UL>
<I>Location</I><BR>
The symposium will be held in a resort place in Antalya, Turkey.<BR>
<I>More information</I><BR>
Professor David M. Maron, Center for Technological Education Holon, POB 58102, Holon 58102, Israel, telefoon: +972-3-502 6666, fax: +972-3-502 6510, e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:barad_r@milk.cteh.ac.il">barad_r@milk.cteh.ac.il</A><P>

