<H3>Symposia en congressen</H3>

<A HREF="#burgers"><B>Burgersdag 1997</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#son"><B>SON-dagen</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#endocrine"><B>Endocrine Active Compounds in Food and Environment</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#euromem"><B>Euromembrane 1997. Progress in Membrane Science and Technology</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#interfaces"><B>Interfaces against Pollution</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#liquid"><B>Liquid-Liquid Two-Phase Flow and Transport Phenomena</B></A>

<P>
<A NAME="burgers"><I>13 januari 1997</I><BR>
<B>Burgersdag 1997</B><BR>
Symposium, J.M. Burgerscentrum, Aula TU Delft.<BR>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD>09.30</TD> <TD>Ontvangst en koffie</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>10.00</TD> <TD>Opening</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>10.10</TD> <TD>Kennis in stroomversnelling, Maes (EZ)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>10.40</TD> <TD>Stromingstechnologie in de petrochemische industrie, Halvers (Shell)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>11.10</TD> <TD>Koffie en postersessie</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>12.00</TD> <TD>Stromingsleer en off-shore technologie, Tan (MARIN)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>12.30</TD> <TD>Stromingsleer in de nonwovenstechnologie, Schipper (Akzo Nobel)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>13.00</TD> <TD>Lunch</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>13.45</TD> <TD>Postersessie</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>14.20</TD> <TD>Stromingsmechanica in turbomachines, Brouwers (Universiteit Twente)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>14.50</TD> <TD>Stromingsleer en voedingsmiddelentechnologie, De Bruijn (Unilever)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>15.20</TD> <TD>Stromingsleer en verbrandingstechnologie, Visser (Gasunie Research)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>15.50</TD> <TD>Slotwoord</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>16.00</TD> <TD>Borrel</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P>
<A NAME="son"><I>20 en 21 januari  1997</I><BR>
<B>SON-dagen</B><BR>
Symposium<BR>
SON Guest Lecture (sponsored by OSPT): <BR>
Prof. Sanjoy Banerjee<BR>
"Compuational Fluid Dynamics for Chemical Engineering Problems"<BR>
<P>
Chemical and petroleum industry-related fluid dynamics is often complicated by effects such as the presence of moving (and deformable) interfaces, chemical reactions and non linear constitutive equations. These add to the usual challenges for industrial CFD posed by complex geometries and (Usually single-phase) turbulence phenomena.
<P>
The lecture will discuss successively more detailed strategies for tackling such problems, based on Reynolds, averaged through large-eddy to direct-numerical simulations. Recent innovations in techniques that allow more detailed simulations of phenomena as complex as breakup and coalescence of interfaces will be outlined, together with illustrations of the role each method can play. It will be shown that not only can such CFD calculations supplement experimental databases and thus aid in design and operation, but also that the more detailed simulations can lead to physical insight that is crucial to modeling complex phenomena, such as multi-phase transport processes.

<P>
<A NAME="endocrine"><I>11 april 1997</I><BR>
<B>Endocrine Active Compounds in Food and Environment:</B><BR>
<B>-setting the research agenda-</B><BR>
Symposium<BR>
<I>Programme in brief:</I><BR>
<UL>
<LI>We offer you a programme in which reasons pro and con are made by respected experts in the field. Among them are: Mrs. Dr. Theo Colburn (author of "Our stolen future"),  prof. Safe from Texas A&M University. Also a member of CEFIC-ECETOC, as a representative of the industry will be present and take part in the discussions.
<LI>Scientific views and strategies, are presented to inform you about the state of the art with respect of endocrine disruption in the fields of (eco)toxicology, endocrinology, epidemiology and foodtechnology.
<LI>A poster market is held which informs you about actual research data, research techniques as well as about research initiatives from various research centres.
<LI>In a forum research strategies will be discussed.
</UL>
<I>Date, place, application:</I><BR>
The symposium is held on April 11, 1997 and will take place in the well equiped Reehorst Congress and Conference Centre in Ede. The symposium fee is Df 300,-- including documentation, coffee/tea, lunch buffet.
<I>More information:</I><BR>
For more information about the symposium programme, please contact: Dr. Bram Brouwer, Dept. Toxicology/ WAU, tel. 0317 - 483971, e-mail:<A HREF="mailto:MenT@sector.spb.wau.nl"> MenT@sector.spb.wau.nl</A>.

<P>
<A NAME="euromem"><I>23 - 27 juni 1997</I><BR>
<B>Euromembrane 1997</B><BR>
<B>Progress in Membrane Science and Technology</B><BR>
The scope of the Symposium will be "new aspects of mem-brane science and technology". The Symposium is directed to scientists concerned with the development and application of new membranes and membrane processes. The program for the Symposium will include invited lectures, poster sessions and oral presentations on the following topics:
<UL>
<LI>Membrane formation
<LI>Membrane characterization
<LI>Gas separation
<LI>Pervaporation
<LI>Liquid membranes
<LI>Catalytic membranes
<LI>Process design
<LI>New materials
<LI>New applications
</UL>
Symposium Secretariat:<BR>
Convention Bureau Basics, P.O. Box 217, NL-7500 AE En-schede, tel. +31 53 4332035, fax +31 53 435 6770, e-mail:<A HREF="mailto:pmst97@basics,utwente.nl"> pmst97@basics,utwente.nl</A>.

<P>
<A NAME="interfaces"><I>10 - 13 augustus 1997</I><BR>
<B>Interfaces against Pollution</B><BR>
International Papers LuW.<BR>
Topics:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Colloid and interface science of particles and contami-nants in the environment (particles and/or polyelectro-lytes and contaminants in aquatic and soil systems).
<LI>Fundamental colloidal and interfacial aspects of moni-toring, remediation and prevention (adsorption, wetting, flotation, micellization, (ad)solubilization, emulsifica-tion).
<LI>Remediation and prevention (waste immobilisation, re-moval of heavy metal ions or organic components, soil characteristics and remediation, recycling and reclama-tion).
<LI>Environmental catalysis/bio-remediation (adsorbent/ca-talyst preparation and characterisation, photo-catalysis near surfaces, micellar catalysis, enzymes on supports, bacterial adhesion).
</UL>

Conference fees:<BR>
The total conference fee covering registration, conference information, abstract book, coffee or tea and all meals (in-cluding the conference dinner) will amount to about Dfl. 600,--.<BR>
Conference secretariat IAP97:<BR>
Fax: +31 (317) 48377, e-mail:<A HREF="mailto:IAP97@fenk.wau.nl"> IAP97@fenk.wau.nl</A>, p.o. Box 8038, 6700 EK Wageningen.

<P>
<A NAME="liquid"><I>3 - 7 november 1997</I><BR>
<B>Liquid-Liquid Two-Phase Flow and Transport Phenomena</B><BR>
Symposium, Antalya, Turkey.<BR>
<I>Objective</I><BR>
The goal of the symposium is to provide a forum for the ex-posure and exchange of ideas, methods, and results in li-quid-liquid flow heat and mass transfer. While papers on all aspects of liquid-liquid phenomena will be welcome, contri-butions are especially invited on the following subjects:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Liquid-liquid systems and applications
<LI>Modeling - flow patterns and flow characteristics
<LI>Modeling - stability and transitions
<LI>Liquid-liquid separation, phenomena and equipment
<LI>Measurement and instrumentation
<LI>Characteristics and effective properties of liquid-liquid systems
<LI>Multi-phase systems
<LI>Surface phenomena
</UL>
<I>Location</I><BR>
The symposium will be held in a resort place in Antalya, Turkey.<BR>
<I>More information</I><BR>
Professor David M. Maron, Center for Technological Edu-cation Holon, POB 58102, Holon 58102, Israel, telefoon: +972-3-502 6666, fax: +972-3-502 6510, e-mail:<A HREF="barad_r @milk.cteh.ac.il"> barad_r @milk.cteh.ac.il</A>.


