<H3>Symposia en congressen</H3>

<A HREF="#distillation"><B>Distillation and Absorption Conferentie</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="#liquid"><B>Liquid-Liquid Two-Phase Flow and Transport Phenomena Symposium</B></A><P>

<A NAME="distillation"><I>8 - 10 september 1997</I><BR>
<B>Distillation and Absorption</B><BR>
Conferentie, MECC Maastricht<BR>
This conference, the sixth in the now well established series, will present the latest developments and identify new directions in Distillation & Absorption, bring practitioners and researchers together, and foster international co-operation. The conference will take place in Maastricht, the first time the event has been held outside the UK. This venue has been especially selected as an international conference centre with excellent transport links te destinations world-wide. This is a rare opportunity to attend a truly international gathering of leading researchers, developers and designers of distillation and absorption hardware, software and processes, to discuss new developments, exchange experiences, and see where the future is leading. For further information, contact: Hans Keuken, Keuken & De Konging b.v., P.O. Box 246, 2600 AE Delft, tel: 015 - 262 2355 fax: 015 - 262 6984.<P>

<A NAME="liquid"><I>3 - 7 november 1997</I><BR>
<B>Liquid-Liquid Two-Phase Flow and Transport Phenomena</B><BR>
Symposium, Antalya, Turkey.<BR>
<I>Objective</I><BR>
The goal of the symposium is to provide a forum for the exposure and exchange of ideas, methods, and results in liquid-liquid flow heat and mass transfer.<BR>
While papers on all aspects of liquid-liquid phenomena will be welcome, contributions are especially invited on the following subjects:
<UL>
<LI>Liquid-liquid systems and applications
<LI>Modeling - flow patterns and flow characteristics
<LI>Modeling - stability and transitions
<LI>Liquid-liquid separation, phenomena and equipment
<LI>Measurement and instrumentation
<LI>Characteristics and effective properties of liquid-liquid systems
<LI>Multi-phase systems
<LI>Surface phenomena
</UL>
<I>Location</I><BR>
The symposium will be held in a resort place in Antalya, Turkey.<BR>
<I>More information</I><BR>
Professor David M. Maron, Center for Technological Education Holon, POB 58102, Holon 58102, Israel, telefoon: +972-3-502 6666, fax: +972-3-502 6510, e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:barad_r@milk.cteh.ac.il">barad_r@milk.cteh.ac.il</A><P>

