<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Holdups in slurry bubble columns</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<TABLE BORDER=0>

        <TR>

        <TD>

<img align=middle src="ospt1.gif">        </TD>

        <TD width = 400 align=middle>

<Font Size = +2><b>Holdups in slurry bubble columns</b></Font></b> </TD>

        </TR>

</TABLE>


<HR size = 0>

<img ALIGN=LEFT src="cr9.gif"> 

Slurry bubble column reactors, used in e.g. Fischer Tropsch and methanol synthesis usually employ fairly fine 

catalyst particles, typically smaller than 100  mm.  Such small particles are finely dispersed in the liquid 

phase and will have the mixing characteristics of the liquid phase. Here the "dense" phase can be considered 

to be the slurry in which the "small" bubbles are dispersed.  As in G-L systems, in the heterogeneous regime 

the dilute phase consisting of "large" bubbles traverse the column at high velocities.  De Swart and Krishna 

(1995) studied the influence of particles concentration on the gas holdup in a slurry bubble column of 0.05 m 

diameter. With increasing slurry concentration the total gas holdup e  is found to decrease significantly and

 regime transition occurs "earlier"; see Fig. 8 (a). The "dilute" phase gas hold-up <i>E</i>b on the other  hand  is

 practically independent of the slurry concentration; cf Fig. 8 (b). 

<br clear=all>

<img src="cr10.gif"> 

<br clear=all>

The decrease in <i>E</i> is almost entirely to be 

attributed to the decrease in the gas voidage of the "small" bubbles, edf. Solid particles enhance the coalescence 

of "small" bubbles but have no  significant effect on the fast-rising "large" bubbles. An acid test of our unified 

model developed for G-S and G-L systems is to predict eb for slurry systems.  A comparison of model predictions with 

experimental data, shown in Fig. 8 (b), testifies to the predictive capability of the model.<p>

<br clear=all>

<hr size=0>

<a href="cr5.html">Read on: Generalized model</a><br>

<a href="cr3.html">Back to: Gas holdup</b><p></a>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl"> OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 02/02/96</CENTER></H6>

