<HEAD><TITLE>The bead string reactor: a dustproof, low pressure drop reactor</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>The bead string reactor: a dustproof, low pressure drop reactor</H2>

<B>PhD student:</B> ir. K&aacute;lm&aacute;n Takfi&aacute;cs (TU Budapest) ((015)-782635)<BR>
<B>Sponsors:</B> SON, KSLA<BR>
<B>Cooperation:</B> KSLA, TU Budapest<BR>
	
<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Introduction</B><BR>
The Bead String Reactor (BSR) is a
new type of gas/solid catalytic reactors. In
the reactor the solid catalyst is fixed on
strings that are arranged parallel to the
flow. The space between the channels
forms a continuous, straight channel
structure.<BR>

<B>Advantages:</B><BR>
<UL>
<LI>a low pressure drop
<LI>good lateral heat and mass transport
<LI>dustproof operation
<LI>a wide range (10-100 %) of voidage
for the design
</UL

<B>Potential drawback:</B><BR>
<UL>
<LI>lower gas-solid mass transfer rate
</UL>

<IMG SRC="kalman1.gif"><P>

<FONT SIZE=-1>The Bead String Reactor (square pitch)</FONT><P>

<B>Potential applications</B><BR>
<UL>
<LI>flue gas treatment
<LI>steam reforming
</UL>

<B>The objective</B><BR>
<UL>
<LI>The development of an engineering
model for the transfer of momentum, heat
and mass, for a suitably chosen chemical
reaction and dust trapping.
<LI>Optimization of the BSR for a model
reaction system
</UL>

<B>Done</B><BR>
A Mathematical model was set up the
parameters of which have been measured
independently.<P>

The model can describe the experiments
adequately. The figures show the
agreement between the experiments and
the two extremes of the model.<P>

<IMG SRC="kalman2.gif"><P>

<FONT SIZE=-1>Parity plots of deNOx experiments in a lab-scale
BSR. a): bead strings modeled as strings of
individual catalyst beads (one extreme of the
model); b): bead strings modeled as 'infinitely'
long catalyst cylinders (other extreme)</FONT><P>

<B>Future work</B><BR>
<UL>
<LI>case studies
</UL>
The project will be completed medio 1996.<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 10/04/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
