<HEAD><TITLE>Selective hydrogenation of benzaldehyde over a monolithic nickel catalyst</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Selective hydrogenation of benzaldehyde over a monolithic nickel catalyst</H2>

<B>Researcher:</B> Adri&euml;tte van de Riet<BR>
<B>Status:</B> AIO<BR>
<B>Started:</B> August 1994<BR>
<B>External support:</B> NIOK, DSM Research<BR>
	
<HR SIZE=0>

<I>Monolithic nickel on alumina catalysts were prepared. The catalysts were tested in a
reactor with an internal recirculation of the reactants. The liquid-phase
hydrogenation of benzaldehyde to benzyl alcohol was used as a test reaction.</I><P>

<B>Introduction</B><BR>
A monolithic catalyst consists of a large number of parallel channels. Frequently
the channel walls are covered with a thin layer of a porous oxide (washcoat). This
washcoat serves as the catalyst carrier. Advantages are a low pressure drop, a large
external surface area and a short diffusion length.<BR>
Monolithic catalysts are widely used for (environmental) gas-phase processes.
However, they are also promising for gas/liquid reactions. In this case operation under
segmented flow conditions provides low external mass transfer resistance.<P>

<B>Experimental</B><BR>
Monolithic nickel on alumina catalysts were prepared. A deposition-precipitation
method was used to load nickel onto the alumina washcoat. Ex-situ reduction and
passivation of the catalysts enabled later <I>in-situ</I> reduction at a lower temperature.<BR>
The catalysts were tested in the
hydrogenation of benzaldehyde to benzyl
alcohol. A reactor with internal recirculation
of the reactants was used. Typical results of
an experiment are given in figure 1.
Benzaldehyde was hydrogenated with very
high selectivity (>99%). When almost all
benzaldehyde      was      converted,
hydrogenolysis of benzyl alcohol to toluene
and water became substantial.<P>

<IMG SRC="adriette1.gif"><P>

Figure 1: Typical result (415 K, 20 bara)<P>

<B>Conclusions and future work</B><BR>
The monolithic catalysts showed a high activity and selectivity. Further
optimization is possible. The hydrogenation of benzaldehyde under segmented flow
conditions will also be studied.<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 10/04/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
</HTML>
