<HEAD><TITLE>PhD-projects Delft</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Process Integration and Control<HR></H2>

<TT><PRE>
Delft University of Technology
Department of Chemical Technology and Material Science
Julianalaan 136
NL 2628 BL Delft

telephone: +31 (0)15 278 4351
fax:       +31 (0)15 278 4452
e-mail:    <A HREF="mailto:c.monna@stm.tudelft.nl">c.monna@stm.tudelft.nl</A>
internet:  <A HREF="http://www.cpt.stm.tudelft.nl/cpt/pi/homepage.html">http://www.cpt.stm.tudelft.nl/cpt/pi/homepage.html</A>
</PRE></TT>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> PhD-projects Delft

<HR>

<H2 ALIGN=center>Delft University of Technology<BR>
Research Group 'Process Systems and Control'
</H2>

Process Systems and Control address the technical aspects of design and operation of chemical plants as a system. The major objective is to develop models and methods for these complex systems as a tool for decision making in design, control and optimization of operation. The group has a tradition in heuristic/conceptual engineering approach as well as the modern analytical/computational means to deal with dynamic chemical process systems.<P>

Areas of research interest:<BR>
<OL TYPE=A>
<LI> Process Design and Analysis<BR>
Uncertainty analysis; Controllability and operability at design stage; Application area: Heat integration and Energy management
<LI> Optimisation of Operations<BR>
On-line use of chem. eng. models; Dynamic modes of operation; Advanced control techniques; Plant wide analysis and control of production modes
<LI> Modelling Methods and Simulation Tools<BR>
Multi-domain modelling; Model validation methods; Modelling and simulation of complex units

<P>

