<HEAD><TITLE>Fiber deposition in the lower parts of the respiratory system</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Fiber deposition in the lower parts of the respiratory system</H2>

<B>PhD student:</B> Y. Zhou, MSc (Tel: +31-15-2785501)<P>
Sections Risk Management & Particle Technology<BR>
Faculty of Chemical Technology & Material Science<BR>
Delft University of Technology<BR>
	
<HR SIZE=0>

In order to investigate fiber deposition behaviour in the lower part of the lung
(8-23rd generation of Weibel, 1963), a trumpet-like granular bed filter was
developed as a model for these parts of the lung with the granular size varying
per layer (van der Put, 1992). The total volume and cross section of the
airspaces in a layer are the same as in the corresponding generation of the
human lung.<P>

The fiber deposition in the lower parts of the lung during inspiration has been
compared theoretically with the deposition of fibers in the granular bed filter
with the similar physical dimensions and equal flow rate. Fiber orientation,
which strongly influences the fiber deposition in a granular bed filter, depends
on the flow situation. The fibers align themselves parallel, in the direction of the
streamlines, when the fluid flow is laminar.<P>

The experimental research starts from spherical particles with the diameter from
0.3 - 0.8&#181;m to compare with the models developed by Boulaud (1991). Three
parameters of the granular bed filter i.e., glass bead diameter, bed height and
total flow rate, were changed separately. The results show that the penetration
of the particles increases with the increase of flow rate and bead diameter, and
decreases with the increase of the bed height as predicted by the model.<P>

Some experiments have been done for fiber deposition in a granular bed filter
to validate the modified model. The results show that it exists a big difference
between the experimental data and the theory. More experimental work is being
done in order to build a new model or modify it again.<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 10/04/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
