<HEAD><TITLE>Measurement of electrocharge of particles</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Measurement of electrocharge of particles</H2>

Research Fellow: Masashi Mathida<P>

Sponsor: NUFFIC. Idemitsu Petroleum<BR>
<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Introduction</B><P>

Charging is a well-known phenomenon
from long time ago. and often observed in
daily life. Though some applications of it
have been successfull in the industrial
processes and measurements, there still
remains many fields to be investigated and
developed.<P>

<B>Objectives of this project</B><P>

This project aims at developing the
measurement of electrocharged particles
to the industrial sensors, such as velocity
sensor, particle counter. tomography, and
so on.<P>

<B>Backgrounds</B><P>

With a movement of a charge or charged
particles, both a electrical field and a
magnetic field are generated. There are
described in following Maxwell's four
equations.<P>

<IMG SRC="masashi1.gif"><P>

These equations can be solved under some
conditions. With the measured signals on
a detector in the fields, the required
informations (ex. velocity, position,
number, charge ....)
of moving particles
can be obtained.<P>

<B>Experimental setup</B><BR>
Figure-I shows a diagram of the set up for
the basic experiment. A charged particle is
generated and introduced to the detector.
Signals from the detector are amplified and
sent to computer.<P>

<IMG SRC="masashi2.gif"><P>

<I>Fig-1 Basic set up</I><P>

Firstly, a single particle is examined with a
single detector. In this stage, sensitivity of
the detector and mathematical model is
to be developed. Secondly, the feed source
will be changed to particles, and
identification of each particle will be
achieved in PC with calculation. Finally.
this system will be extended to particles
with many sensors and positional
informations also will be obtained in
real-time response.<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 10/04/96</CENTER></H6>

