<HEAD><TITLE>PhD-projects Delft</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Section Heat transfer<HR></H2>

<TT><PRE>
Delft University of Technology
Faculty of Applied Physics
Heat Transfer Section
Lorentzweg 1
P.O. Box 5046
NL 2600 GA Delft

telephone: +31 (0)15 278 1448
fax:       +31 (0)15 278 1204
internet:  <A HREF="http://duttwte.tn.tudelft.nl:8080/trwthome.html">http://duttwte.tn.tudelft.nl:8080/trwthome.html</A>
</PRE></TT>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> PhD-projects Delft

<HR>
<H2 ALIGN=center>Delft University of  Technology</H2>

<H2 ALIGN=center>Research Group 'Heat Transfer'</H2>

<B>Permanent Staff</B><BR>
prof.dr.dipl.-ing. K. Hanjalic<SUP>*</SUP><BR>
prof.ir. C,J, Hoogendoorn<SUP>*</SUP><BR>
prof.dr. D.J.E.M. Roekaerts<BR>
dr.ir. C.C.J. Bart<SUP>*</SUP><BR>
dr. J.J.Ph. Elich<BR>
dr.ir. Th.H. van der Meer<BR>
dr.ir. T.W.J. Peeters<P>

<B>Research Scientists</B><BR>
ir. R.E.J. van den Bercken<BR>
ir. G.P. Boerstoel<BR>
ir. H.S. Dol<BR>
ir. F.I.E. Doolaar<BR>
dipl.-ing. I. Hadzic<BR>
dipl.-ing. S. Kenjeres<BR>
ir. E. Meinders<BR>
ir. P. Nooren<BR>
ir. R. Verweij<BR>
ir. H.A. Wouters<P>

<SUP>*</SUP> participating in OSPT<P>

<B>Research Themes</B><P>

<I>Convection, diffusion, radiation and turbulent flames</I><BR>
Convective heat and mass transport studies with numerical simulation models and experimental validation with optical and other techniques. Turbulent combustion and flames is a main topic studied. The emphasis is on combustion of natural gas. Applications are related to burners and furnaces for special high temperature furnaces.<BR>
On thermal radiation studies are made of radiation from flames in furnaces.<P>

<I>Heat conduction</I><BR>
Study on thermal conduction in and thermal aging of insulation foams, like polyurethane foams. Variables studied are morphology, gas blowing agents and radiative properties. In relation to aging the diffusion absorption in the polymeric is investigated. The practical application is the search for CFC-alternatives as blowing agent.<P>

<I>Facilities</I><BR>
Computational research covers fundamentals of flow and chemistry modelling in non-reacting and reacting turbulent flows, as well as model application to complex industrial problems. The experimental programme includes advanced flow measuring techniques (laser doppler anemometry, laser interferometry), techniques for flame diagnostics (LIF and CARS), measurements of conductivity and radiative properties (infrared thermography), surface temperature (liquid crystals), and heat flux.<P>

<B>Industrial Research</B><P>

Industrial research is going on in all off the above mentioned fields. Software for large computational fluid dynamics and heat and mass transfer studies has been developed and is available. Also radiative heat transfer codes are in use. For industrial research these codes are available for particular problems in technology.<P>

