<HEAD><TITLE>Phd-projects Eindhoven</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Laboratory for Separation Technology<HR></H2>

<TT><PRE>
Technical University of Eindhoven
Faculty of Chemical Technology
P.O. Box 513
NL 5600 MB Eindhoven

telephone: +31 (0)40 247 2973
fax:       +31 (0)40 244 6104
e-mail:    <A HREF="mailto:lst@chem.tue.nl">lst@chem.tue.nl</A>
internet:  <A HREF="http://www.tcp.chem.tue.nl/Kerkhof/index.html">http://www.tcp.chem.tue.nl/Kerkhof/index.html</A>
</PRE></TT>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> PhD-projects Eindhoven

<HR>

<H3>LABORATORY FOR SEPARATION PROCESS AND TRANSPORT PHENOMENA</H3>

Within the department of Chemical Engineering of the Eindhoven University of Technology, a team of about 20 persons is engaged in research on the technology of separation processes. The research group is also involved in courses and training. Annually, the relatively high number of 20 students graduate on subjects studied by the group. In the research projects the attention is focussed on the multilevel, multidistributed nature of the phenomena and processes. The goal of the research is a fundamental understanding that can be incorporated in process and equipment models, thus enabling firm-based design and optimization of separation processes for often complex media. On all levels, ranging from micro- to macro scale, theoretical modelling is interweaved with experimental work. Advanced research facilities have been realised and are still growing, both on laboratory and pilot-scale. The group has established strong, still widening contacts with other institutions at home and abroad, and firm, mutual interests with industry and government offices.<P>

<H3>RESEARCH TOPICS</H3>

<UL>
<B>Dewatering and drying processes</B><BR>
dr.ir. Jan Coumans &amp; dr.ir. Ton van der Zanden
<LI><I>drying of deformable media</I> (ir. Bas Kroes)
<LI><I>modelling quality in spray drying</I> (ir. Frank Kieviet)
<LI><I>diffusion modelling in liquids and complex media</I> (ir. Irma van de Ven-Lucassen)
<LI><I>sludge dewatering</I>
<LI><I>drying of paper</I>
<LI><I>drying of textile</I>
</UL>

<UL>
<B>Application of external fields</B><BR>
dr.ir. Krzysztof Ptasinski
<LI><I>electrostatic coalescence</I>
<LI><I>electrostatic gas dispersion</I> (ing. Ton Staring)
<LI><I>large scale electrophoresis</I> (ir. Erik van Nunen)
</UL>

<UL>
<B>Sorption and membrane processes</B><BR>
ir. Marius Vorstman
<LI><I>adsorption from solutions onto activated carbon</I>
<LI><I>interaction of components near a membrane</I> (ir. Frank Pijpers)
<LI>alternative sorbers and carriers
</UL>

