<HEAD><TITLE>Phd-projects Eindhoven</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Dispersions and Chemical Reactors<HR></H2>

<TT><PRE>
Technical University of Eindhoven
Faculty of Chemical Technology
P.O. Box 513
NL 5600 MB Eindhoven

telephone: +31 (0)40 247 3003
fax:       +31 (0)40 244 6104
internet:  <A HREF="http://www.tcp.chem.tue.nl/Thoenes/index.html">http://www.tcp.chem.tue.nl/Thoenes/index.html</A>
</PRE></TT>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> PhD-projects Eindhoven

<HR>

Research is carried out in the field of Chemical Reaction Engineering, especially focussed on gas-solid and liquid-solid dispersions. The main subjects are fluidisation, hydrodynamics of low and high viscosity liquids, especially in stirred tanks, precipitation and agglomeration processes, and polymer reaction engineering. Pilot scale equipment is available for part of the experimental work.<P>


<UL>
<B>FLUIDISATION</B> (ir. H.W. Piepers)
<LI>Gas-solid fluidisation, mixing, circulation
<LI>Heat- and mass transfer
<LI>Fluidised bed granulation
</UL>


<UL>
<B>STIRRED TANKS</B> (ir. J.G. Wijers)<BR>
<B>Turbulent flow</B>
<LI>Flow- and energy-dissipation profiles (v and e), 2D-Laser Doppler Velocimetry
<LI>Flow-visualisation, laser induced fluorescense
<LI>Micro- and meso-mixing
</UL>

<UL>
<B>Precipitation of inorganic salts</B> (<I>ir. J. Schoenmakers</I>)
<LI>Influence meso-mixing on nucleation (v- and e-profiles)
<LI>Particle size distributions
</UL>

<UL>
<B>Suspension of solids</B>
<LI>CFD modelling
<LI>Flow profiles by refractive index matching
</UL>

<UL>
<B>POLYMERISATION REACTORS</B> (dr. J. Meuldijk)<BR>
<B>Reaction and micromixing in viscous flow</B>
<LI>Flow patterns, visualisation
<LI>Micro-mixing: modelling of flow and diffusion
</UL>

<UL>
<B>Emulsion polymerisation</B> (<I>ir. F. van den Boomen</I>, <I>ir. M.F. Kemmere</I>)
<LI>Kinetics, particle formation and coagulation
<LI>Batch-, semi-batch and CSTR
<LI>Pulsed Packed Column: axial &amp; radial mixing, influence of kinetics
<LI>Copolymerisation: batch, continuous and PPC
<LI>Scaling-up
</UL>

<UL>
<B>PREPARATION OF MONODISPERSE PARTICLES</B> (dr. A. Eshuis)
<LI>Controlled precipitation (spherical agglomerates of crystals)
<LI>Emulsifier-free emulsion polymerisation (part. > 1 mm), including recycling of process water during emulsion polymerisation
<LI>Dispersion and suspension polymerisation
</UL>

<I>(in italics: names of graduate students preparing for doctor's thesis)</I><P>

