<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Design of a multi stage fluid bed</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Design of a multi stage fluid bed</H2>

<B>AIO-2:</B> ir. R.G.J. Willems (040 - 2474968)<BR>
<B>Supervisor:</B> prof. dr. ir. D. Thoenes, ir. H.W. Piepers<BR>
<B>Sponsor:</B> DSM<BR>
	
<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Introduction</B><P>

During production of powders organic
solvents are frequently used. Traces of the
solvents stay in the powder afar production.
Considering the environmental impact of
organic solvents, they have to be removed
from the powders.<P>

<B>Objective</B><P>

A multi stage fluid bed is one of the options
for the removal of the organic solvents.
However little is yet known about multi
stage fluid beds. The objective of this
project is to model and design a multi stage
fluid bed to remove organic solvents from
powders.<P>

<B>Experiments</B><P>

In Figure 1 the experimental set up is drawn
schematically. The diameter of the column
is 15 cm.<P>

<IMG SRC="willems1.gif"><P>

<B>Figure 1: Experimental set up</B><P>

Experiments have been performed to
determine the stable operation area. The
results are shown in Figure 2.<P>

<IMG SRC="willems2.gif"><P>

<B>Figure 2: Stable operation area</B><BR>
<I>diamonds = critical velocity squares = flooding velocity</I><P>

Also, the maximum operating temperature
and the dynamic behaviour of the column,
for example the response of the bed on a
short gas stop, will be studied<P>

<B>Modelling</B><P>

Using the results of the experiments a
model will be made to simulate the fluid
bed. The amount of stages needed will be
determined and the operating setpoints will
be optimised with this model.<P>

<B>Design</B><P>

Finally, a multi stage fluid bed will be
designed for a desired capacity, with the
constraints given by the experiments and
the model.<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 10/04/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
