<HEAD><TITLE>Computer applications in chemical engineering</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Computer applications in chemical engineering</H2>

<CENTER>Dr.ir. A.G.J. van der Ham</CENTER><BR>
	
<HR SIZE=0>


<I>General goal:</I><BR>
Modelling, simulation, design and optimization of chemical processes as well as chemical reactors
using commercial software tools like Aspen Plus, Hysim, Speedup, SimuSolv etc., in order to
obtain the technical and economical most feasible configuration.<P>

<I>Projects finished or in progress:</I><BR>
<UL>
<LI>Production of methanol using the RSIPR concept (reaction system with interstage product
removal) with TEGDME, acetamide or other organic solvents as the absorption liquids.

<LI>Production of ethylene oxide: the influence of an increasing oxygen concentration on the reactor
and process design, and the technical and economical feasibility of the EO process.

<LI>Feasibility study for different types of heat pumps (e.g. bottom flash, top vapour recompression
and absorption heat pumps, and the absorption heat transformator) and there application in
chemical industry.

<LI>Steam stripping of soils contaminated with organic compounds (NAPL): modelling and
experiments.

<LI>Industrial application of ceramic membranes and there economical feasibility. The
dehydrogenation of ethyl benzene to styrene is taken as a test case.

<LI>Regenerative, high temperature desulfurization of coal gas: a thermodynamic and kinetic study.
First potential metal, metal oxide and carbonate sorbents for the regenerative H2S removal were
selected based on a thermodynamic study of the process using Aspen Plus. Different regeneration
routes were investigated. Second, the regenerative desulfurization process, consisting of a
circulating fluidized bed absorber and a fluidized bed regenerator, using iron oxide as a sorbent
was modelled in Aspen Plus.

<LI>Feasibility of high temperature desulfurization in a KV-STEG power plant (coal gasification
combined with a steam and gas turbine). The previous described user module for a
desulfurization process is incorporated in a Aspen Plus model of a KV-STEG power plant.

<LI>Recycling processes for PVC, Polystyrene and mixed plastic waste. Back to monomer as well as
back to feed stock processes are investigated using different types of reactors e.g. fluidized bed
(Kaminsky), circulating fluidized bed (Batelie) and the spinning cone reactor.

<LI>Technical and economical feasibility study of two hydrogen peroxide processes (Anthrachinon
process versus Arco process).
</UL>

<I>Future projects:</I><BR>
<UL>
<LI>Air stripping of soils contaminated with organic compounds (NAPL): modelling and experiments

<LI>Process/reactor modelling with the commercial software tools Speedup and gPROMS.

<LI>Recycling processes for mixed plastic waste. Back to monomer as well as back to feed stock
processes are investigated with special attention for the product separation and purification
section.

<LI>Organic Rankine Cycle: selection criteria for active solvents and solvent mixtures.
</UL>

