<DOCOLDNO>IA011-000119-B031-28</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://utct.ct.utwente.nl:80/~ospt/minipost95/rug/harth.html 130.89.50.60 19970216195045 text/html 2641
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Sunday, 16-Feb-97 19:44:09 GMT
Server: NCSA/1.3
MIME-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/html
Last-modified: Wednesday, 23-Oct-96 06:55:06 GMT
Content-length: 2458
</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>The influence of the gas relative humidity on the mixing and segregation in gas-solid fluidised beds</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>The influence of the gas relative humidity on the mixing and segregation in gas-solid fluidised beds</H2>

<CENTER>G.P. Hartholt, A.C. Hoffmann and L.P.B.M. Janssen, Department of Chemical Engineering, University of Groningen, Nijenborgh 4, 9747AG Groningen, The Netherlands.</CENTER>

<HR SIZE=0>



<B>Introduction.</B><P>

Physical particle properties that influence the mixing in fluidised beds:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>size
<LI>density
<LI>shape
<LI>cohesivity (interparticle forces)
</UL>

<I>Does the increased cohesivity due to adsorption of water influence the mixing ?</I><P>

<B>Experimental.</B><P>

Influence of the gas relative humidities for 285 &#181;m and 565 &#181;m glass ballotini on:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>minimum fluidisation velocities
<LI>mixing
</UL>

Newly developed apparatus has the following features:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>wide range of precisely controlled flow rates
<LI>wide range of controlled gas relative humidities
<LI>constant gas temperature
<LI>no pressure fluctuations
</UL>

<IMG SRC="harth1.gif"><P>

<B>Results.</B><P>

Increasing gas relative humidity:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Bed voidage increases
<LI>Pressure drop decreases
<LI>U<SUB>mf</SUB> increases (see figure)
<LI>Mixing decreases (see figures)
</UL>

<IMG SRC="harth2.gif"><P>
<IMG SRC="harth3.gif"><P>
<IMG SRC="harth4.gif"><P>

<B>Discussion and conclusions.</B><P>

Fluidisation with humid gas increases interparticle forces which results in:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>an increase of voidage
<LI>an increase of U<SUB>mf</SUB>
<LI>a decrease of mixing
</UL>

From agreement with experimental jetsam fraction in the segregated layer with predictions using Cheung's (1974) equation for the U<SUB>mf</SUB> of binary mixtures<P>

<IMG SRC="harth5.gif"><P>

it can be concluded that the mixing in beds with higher interparticle forces:<BR>
<UL>
<LI> still attributed to the bubble flow
<LI>is not improved due to reduced segregation of individual jetsam particles
</UL>

<FONT SIZE=-1>Cheung, L., Nienow, A.W., Rowe, P.N., 1974, Chem. Eng. Sci., Vol. 29, 1301.</FONT><P>

<IMG SRC="rug.gif"><P>

