<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Improving the separation efficiency of industrial scale cyclones for small particles</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Improving the separation efficiency of industrial scale cyclones for small particles</H2>

<B>Psot-doc:</B> Dr. M.B. Ray<BR>
<B>Researchers:</B> Ir. A. Plomp, Ing. P. Luning, Dr. A.C. Hoffmann<BR>
<B>Principal:</B> Bureau M+I, Amsterdam; Sponsor: NOVEM<BR>
	
<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Introduction</B><P>

A new approach to reduce dust emissions from industrial scale gas cyclones utilising the strong swirl present in the vortex finder.<P>

The collection takes place in a so-called 'Post-cyclone' (PoC). This is sketched in Figure 1. The PoC is placed above the cyclone gas exhaust (vortex finder). A cylindrical screen separates the inner chamber from the outer one. Particles separated and exiting in the bleed flow can, for instance, be returned to the process stream.<P>

<IMG SRC="ray1.gif"><P>

<I>Fig. 1 Sketch of the PoC (not to scale)</I><P>

<B>Results</B><P>

The operation of the PoC was investigated by:<P>

1.	CFD<BR>
2.	Experiments in pilot-scale equipment<P>

The flow pattern in the PoC was simulated using FLUENT. The calculations showed that a recirculatory flowpattern around the screen and in the outer chamber makes for a long particle residence time in the PoC, enhancing agglomeration and therefore particle capture.<P>

Grade-efficiency curves for the PoC and the cyclone itself were determined experimentally and also predicted by numerical simulation using particle tracking. Predicted and experimental curves for the PoC are compared in Figure 2.<P>

<IMG SRC="ray2.gif"><P>

<I>Fig. 2 Experimental and predicted grade-efficiency curves for the PoC</I><P>

<B>Further Studies</B><P>

The PoC is being characterised for varying operational and geometrical parameters using both on-line and off-line particle sizing for the generation of grade-efficiency curves. The efficiency of the system will be tested on various industrially important powders.<P>

<IMG SRC="rug.gif"><P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl"> OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 18/03/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
