<HEAD><TITLE>The implementation of quantitative risk assessment in HACCP as a tool for the production of safe foods</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>The implementation of quantitative risk assessment in HACCP as a tool for the production of safe foods</H2>

<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Introduction</B><P>
The Hazard Analysis Critical Control Point (HACCP) system is mainly used in a qualitative manner. The aim of this project is the realization of a quantitative approach of this system. This will be done by implementation of Quantitative Risk Assessment (<B>QRA</B>) for food products in the existing HACCP system.<P>

<HR SIZE=0>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD>
<B>Methods</B><P>

In the development of QRA an objective method will be made for:<P>
<OL>
<LI>ientification of hazards<BR>
<LI>estimation of the average amount of pathogens<BR>
<LI>estimation of the probability of presence of pathogens<BR>
<LI>conduction of a failure analysis<P>
</OL>
As shown in figure 1 combination of the method with dose-response data will result in QRA.<BR>
</TD>
<TD>
<IMG SRC="suzanne1.gif"><P>
figure 1. Combination of objective method with dose-response data
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<HR SIZE=0>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD>
<B>Results</B><P>

A decision tree (figure 2) has been established by which the mentioned objective method in QRA can be established.<P>

For a good estimate of the hazards in food products and the control of hazards the decision tree will be consulted at least twice. Firstly to roughly estimate the main hazards and secondly to perform a more detailed hazard analysis to find less obvious hazards.<P>

The quantitative HACCP system is being implemented into a computer program to make it easy accessible for users.<P>
</TD>
<TD>
<IMG SRC="suzanne2.gif"><P>
figure 2. Decision tree for determination of microbiological hazard
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<HR SIZE=0>
<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD>
Wageningen Agricultural University<BR>
Food and Bioprocess Engineering Group<BR>
the Netherlands
</TD>
<TD>
<IMG SRC="w.gif" WIDTH=38 HEIGHT=83>
</TD>
<TD>
Suzanne J.C. van Gerwen<BR>
Marcel H. Zwietering<BR>
Klaas van 't Riet
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl"> OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 14/03/96</CENTER></H6>

