<HEAD><TITLE>Reactor design for the enzymatic synthesis of oligosaccharides</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Reactor design for the enzymatic synthesis of oligosaccharides</H2>

<B>PhD-fellow:</B> Ir. Floor Boon<BR>
<B>Project term:</B> May 1995 - May 1999<BR>
<B>Sponsor:</B> ABON<BR>
	
<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Introduction</B><BR>
There is a growing interest in the synthesis of oligosaccharides for application in 'functional foods'. Oligosaccharides are non digestible and effective for the growth of Bifidobacterium in the intestinal canal. For the production of oligosaccharides, glycosidases can be used as catalysts. During this reaction water is produced as by-product and the equilibrium lies unfavourable. A reactor has to be designed in which the synthesis of oligosaccharides takes place. To achieve this, knowledge of the kinetics and the equilibrium position is necessary.<P>

<B>Aim</B><BR>
The main objective of this project is to design a suitable reactor for the enzymatic synthesis of oligosaccharides. Development and validation of methods and models to describe the equilibrium and the enzyme kinetics are necessary to achieve this aim.<P>

<B>Research</B><BR>
A model system is chosen to study kinetics, equilibrium and the effect of different process variables on the oligosaccharides formation. This model system is the enzymatic production of trisaccharides with the enzyme beta-galactosidase and lactose as a substrate (see figure 1). In literature, formation of the enzyme-galactose-complex is often described. This enzymcomplex can react with water to give the hydrolysis product galactose, or it can react with lactose to give the transferase product trisaccharide. Initially the model will be kept simple, however, it might be necessary to include extra steps, for example production of tetra-, and pentasaccharides.<P>

<IMG SRC="floor1.gif"><P>

<B>Figure 1.</B> Reaction scheme of the enzymatic production of trisaccharides with lactose as substrate (lact= lactose, E= enzyme, glu= glucose, gal= galactose, tri= trisaccharides).<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl"> OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 16/02/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
</HTML>
