<H3>Process Development School Enschede Courses<HR></H3>

In the first part of the actual course six courses have to be completed. The first and the fourth of the here described courses are obliged.<P>

<OL>

<B><LI>Pilot plant design</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. W.P.M. van Swaaij

<B><LI>Advanced separation techniques</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. L.L. van Dierendonck

<B><LI>Polymer technology</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. L.P.B.M. Janssen

<B><LI>Advanced reactor design and reactors for extreme conditions</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. K.R. Westerterp

<B><LI>Reactor models and scale-up of multiphase reactors</B><BR>
<A HREF="http://chte26.chem.rug.nl/scistaff/beenack.html">Prof. dr. ir. A.A.C.M. Beenackers</A> / <A HREF="http://ctwww.chem.uva.nl/cr/kris.htm">Prof. dr. R. Krishna</A>

<B><LI>Industrial catalysis</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. J.A. Moulijn

<B><LI>Rotating equipment</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. J.J.H. Brouwers /  Dr. ir. J.B. Jonkers

<B><LI>Energy and environment in the industry</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. G.G. Hirs

<B><LI>Design of separation processes for multicomponent systems</B><BR>
<A HREF="http://ctwww.chem.uva.nl/cr/kris.htm">Prof.dr. R. Krishna </A> Prof.dr.ir. T. Reith / Prof. ir. J.A. Wesselingh

<LI><A HREF="http://ctwww.chem.uva.nl/cr/unified.htm"><B>A unified approach to mass transfer</B><BR>
</A> <A HREF="http://ctwww.chem.uva.nl/cr/kris.htm">Prof. dr. R. Krishna </A> / Prof. ir. J.A. Wesselingh

<B><LI>Numerical methods in chemical engineering</B><BR>
<A HREF=ftp://omnigate.clarkson.edu/pub/chemsep/taylor.html>Prof. R. Taylor</A> / dr. ir. H.J.C. Hoefsloot / dr. ir. J.A.M. Kuipers

<B><LI>Process control for process technologists</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. B. Roffel

<B><LI>Thermodynamics for process technologists</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. J. de Swaan Arons / dr. ir. Th.W. de Loos

<B><LI>Economic evaluation of processes and projects</B><BR>
Prof. dr. ir. K. Asselbergs

<B><LI><I>In preparation</I>: Computational flu&iuml;d dynamics</B><BR>

</OL><P>

