<HEAD><TITLE>Process Development School Enschede</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H3>The course process plant design of the Process Development Course<HR></H3>

<H3><IMG SRC="../../pic/fabriek.gif"> Process plant design</A></H3>

<B>Prof. dr. ir. H. van den Berg</B><BR> 

During a period of four months attention will be paid to the design of a chemical plant. During an intensive training period methods will be given for the design of processes. Several subjects will be discussed like: draft design, dividing a project into <A HREF="phases.gif">phases</A>, material- and energybalances , flowdiagrams, equipment specifications, environmental problematic, safety- and governmentrules.<P>
Special aspects will be explained by specialists from the industry. During several workshops the development of flowsheets and the design of apparatus will be illustrated by using "state of the art" computer software.<P>
After the course a process design will be made in groups of two persons. After a first reconnoitering a working schedule has to be made and the tasks will be divided. During the project the design will become a defined packet. In some cases a cost-estimate has to be made at the end of the project.<P>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="..\..\pic\home.gif"></A> Process Development School Enschede

