<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>IAT: Consulting</TITLE>
<! -- Created: June 11, 1996 by Chad Kearsley -- >
<! -- Revised: July 15, 1996 -- >

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F" LINK="#006700" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#EE0000">

<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/iatlogo.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=5  ALT="IAT" WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=65 VALIGN=TOP>
	

<A NAME="top"></A>

<TABLE  ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR><TD>
<A HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/media/navigate.map"><IMG SRC="http://www.iat.unc.edu/media/gifs/navigate.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#navigate" ISMAP ALIGN=RIGHT></A>

<MAP NAME="navigate">
<!-- #$-:Image Map file created by Map THIS! -->
<!-- #$-:Map THIS! free image map editor by Todd C. Wilson -->
<!-- #$-:Please do not edit lines starting with "#$" -->
<!-- #$VERSION:1.30 -->
<!-- #$DESCRIPTION:IAT Web Site Navigational Toolbar -->
<!-- #$AUTHOR:Chad Kearsley -->
<!-- #$DATE:Thu Jul 18 11:27:42 1996 -->
<!-- #$PATH:M:\docs\WWW\media\gifs\ -->
<!-- #$GIF:navigate.gif -->
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="13,1,56,22" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/index.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="58,2,99,22" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/general/new.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="102,0,160,23" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/search/search.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="162,0,239,22" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/feedback/feedback.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="241,1,293,23" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/general/about.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="294,1,374,23" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/cybrary/cybrary.html">
</MAP>

</TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<PRE>	

</PRE>
<CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2><FONT SIZE=+3>C</FONT>onsulting </FONT> </STRONG></CENTER>
<BR>
<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH="100%" CELLSPACE=1 CELLPADDING=1>
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="50%">


<DL>
<DT><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/diabull.gif" WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10 HSPACE="5"><STRONG><A HREF="#techbrief">Technology Briefings</A></STRONG></DT>


<DT><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/diabull.gif" WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10 HSPACE="5"><STRONG><A HREF="#focusing">"Focusing Your Vision" Sessions</A></STRONG></DT>

</DL>
<BR>For more information on the IATs technology planning and consulting services, contact Nancy Dooly, 919-405-1955 or <A HREF="mailto:nancyd.iat@mhs.unc.edu">nancyd.iat@mhs.unc.edu</A>. 
</TD>

<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH="440">
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/1X17pix.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="17" HEIGHT="235">

<P>The IAT specializes in helping educational institutions understand ways in which they can use technology strategically to address the most challenging issues of today's world - quality, cost and access. We offer several types of consulting services to help faculty, staff and administrators implement or evaluate their school's technology planning process. Follow a link at left to find out more about that particular service.
</TABLE>
</TABLE>
<PRE>
</PRE>





<BR><BR>
<BR><CENTER><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/2X2pix.gif"WIDTH="400" HEIGHT="1"></CENTER>
<BR><BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="techbrief"><CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2>Technology Briefings</FONT></STRONG></CENTER></A>

<P> <STRONG>Technology Briefings</STRONG> provide an overview of the state of the technology as it applies to education. Participants will see demonstrations of various technologies that can be used to create distributed learning environments. These technologies include new tools on the Internet and the World Wide Web, collaborative and groupware applications such as computer conferencing, multimedia courseware, desktop video, etc. Some of these sessions can also be conducted with hands-on experience for the participants. The Technology Briefings serve as an introduction to faculty, staff, and administrators who want to see and understand how technology can be used in the teaching and learning process. Because of the number of people involved, and the networking and technologies necessary for these briefings, we suggest you bring a group to the IAT for these sessions. Special topic sessions, such as Student Mobile Computing or Distributed Learning Initiatives can also be arranged.
<BR><BR>
<A HREF="#top">[Back to the top]</A>

<BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="focusing"><CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2>"Focusing Your Vision" Sessions</FONT></STRONG></CENTER></A>

<P> <STRONG>"Focusing Your Vision" Sessions</STRONG> are useful in the beginning of a technology planning initiative or any time during the process when the planning direction or objective has become unclear. Vision sessions are facilitated by an IAT consultant who conducts a dialogue with a selected group of key campus players in the technology planning process or initiative. By guiding the group through a discussion of their and the institutions goals, values, objectives and priorities, the consultant is able to help the group define the situations in which technology can be most strategically employed and to prioritize the steps they must take to deploy technology successfully. Vision sessions are a particularly good way to follow up Technology Briefings. They can also be conducted separately at the IAT or on a client campus. They work best, however, when the group participating shares a common understanding of how technology works as an enabler in creating teaching and learning environments.
<BR><BR>
<A HREF="#top">[Back to the top]</A>

<BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>


<BR>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/2X2pix.gif"WIDTH="400" HEIGHT="1"></CENTER>
