<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH="440">
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/1X17pix.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="17" HEIGHT="335">

<P>The IAT produces a wide selection of electronic publications on topics of interest to educators in the information age. Included are articles covering educational technology and pedagogy in the new age written by resident faculty and technical staff; over 40 information resource guides compiled by our Information Resources Group; new and archived issues of the popular <EM>IAT Infobits</EM> - a monthly electronic newsletter that contains a detailed listing of information technology and instruction technology sources from around the world; and archived issues of the Institute newsletter, Briefings. The IAT also produces videotapes of its educational broadcast series. Find out more about any of the IAT's publications or videos by following a link at left.

