<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH="440">
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/1X17pix.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="17" HEIGHT="300">

<P>Our faculty and staff are nationally recognized for their leadership in instructional technology and are continually active in the creation of tools and initiatives to further the strengthening of education in the information age. Recent activities include participation in initiating and implementing EDUCOM's National Learning Infrastructure Initiative, development of award-winning software programs in French and Mathematics, research into new approaches for distributed and distance learning, and the creation of new software tools that simplify multimedia authoring and the distribution of software via the World Wide Web. To find out more about any of our departmental members and activities, follow the links at left.

