<H3><A NAME="author">About the Author</A></H3>

<P>Kathryn is currently Senior Analyst for Distributed Learning Environments with the Institute for Academic Technology.  Previously, she was Director of Special Projects for the Office of Information Technology at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.  Previously she was Director of Instructional Technologies at the University, and before that the Associate Director of the Media and Instructional Support Center.  She has a B.F.A. in Directing for Theatre and an M.A. in Communications, both from UNC-CH.  During her involvement with the Media and Instructional Support Center, Kathryn developed the concept of the Master Classroom as part of the Classroom Improvement Program which she co-administers for the campus.  In her role as Director of Special Projects, Kathryn is currently working with projects concerning the development and networking of multimedia databases.  She also continues to administer Master Classroom development, as well as campus Distance Education projects.  <A HREF="mailto:kathryn_conway@unc.edu">kathryn_conway@unc.edu</A>

