</UL>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="6"></A><STRONG><EM>Consortia, Associations, and Related Professional Organizations</EM></STRONG>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><STRONG>ACSDE -- American Center for the Study of Distance Education (Penn State)</STRONG><BR>
Seeks to promote distance education research, study, scholarship, and teaching and to serve as a clearinghouse for the dissemination of knowledge about distance education. <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.cde.psu.edu/DE/ACSDE/ACSD.htm">http://www.cde.psu.edu/DE/ACSDE/ACSD.htm</A>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>ADEC Distance Learning Consortium</STRONG><BR>
A national consortium of state universities and land grant institutions providing high quality
and economic distance education programs and services via the latest and most appropriate
information technologies. <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ces.ncsu.edu/adec/">http://www.ces.ncsu.edu/adec/</A>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>The Commonwealth of Learning</STRONG><BR>
Purpose is to create and widen access to education and to improve its quality, utilizing
distance education techniques and associated communications technologies to meet the particular
requirements of the 53 Commonwealth member countries. <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.col.org/">http://www.col.org/</A>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>International University Consortium</STRONG><BR>
The International University Consortium (IUC) is a partnership of colleges, universities, and
educational agencies throughout the world that develop and use media-assisted course packages
for distance and open learning programs. <BR>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>Institute for Distance Education</STRONG><BR>
Coordinates and facilitates the growth of distance education capabilities within the University of Maryland System; administered by the Office of Instructional Development at University of Maryland University College.<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.umuc.edu/ide/ide.html">http://www.umuc.edu/ide/ide.html</A>
<P>
<LI><A NAME="smartstates"></A><STRONG>SmartStates Virtual University</STRONG><BR>
SmartStates was created by western state governors as a mechanism to manage change for the
benefit of government, business, and citizens. One of its projects is Virtual University, a regional virtual university to be operating by June 1997 through which instruction will accessible at the learner's convenience via advanced technology.<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.concerto.com/smart/vu/vu.html">http://www.concerto.com/smart/vu/vu.html</A>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>South Bay Advanced Educational Technology Consortium (ADTECH)</STRONG><BR>
A union of schools, businesses and community to unite resources and provide quality educational services to the diverse areas of the South Santa Monica Bay Communities, Los Angeles County, California. <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.commpages.com/adtech/">http://www.commpages.com/adtech/</A>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>Southeastern Pennsylvania Consortium for Information Technology and Training</STRONG><BR>
Comprised of eight small Pennsylvania collges.
<P>
<LI><STRONG>Southwest Center for Advanced Technological Study</STRONG><BR>
Comprised of institutions in Texas, Oklahoma, and New Mexico.
<P>
<LI><STRONG>United States Distance Learning Association</STRONG><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.usdla.org/">http://www.usdla.org/</A>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>Western Cooperative for Educational Telecommunications</STRONG>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>Western Governors' Association and Western Interstate Commission for Higher Education (WICHE)</STRONG><BR>
Working to create the "Western Virtual University." <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.wiche.edu/telecom/telecom.htm">http://www.wiche.edu/telecom/telecom.htm</A> (See also <A HREF="#smartstates">SmartStates Virtual University</A>.)
<P>
Also supports Western Brokering Project to test and refine a plan to build an ongoing capacity
to "broker" the educational resources of western colleges and universities and to make higher
education more widely available to underserved and placebound students throughout the region
through the use of existing telecommunications networks. <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.wiche.edu/broker/bppage.htm">http://www.wiche.edu/broker/bppage.htm</A>
</UL>
<P>
