205-1 Stewart Street<BR>
Ottawa, Ontario<BR>
K1N 6H7 Canada
<P>
More Journals in Distance Education<BR>
<A HREF="http://www-icdl.open.ac.uk/info/journals.html">http://www-icdl.open.ac.uk/info/journals.html</A>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="5"><STRONG>AskERIC Reference Service</STRONG>
<P>
AskERIC is an Internet-based question-answering service for teachers,
library media specialists, administrators, and others involved in
education from ERIC, the Educational Resources Information Center, a
federally-funded national information system that provides access to an
extensive body of education-related resources, including distance learning topics. The hallmark of AskERIC
is the human intermediary, who interacts with the information seeker.
Each year the ERIC staff answers more than 120,000 inquires--responding to queries within 48 working hours. The benefit of the human-mediated service is that it
allows AskERIC staff to determine the precise information needs of the
client and to present an array of relevant resources, both from the
ERIC system and from the vast resources of the Internet.
<P>
The link to the AskERIC service on the
Web is <A HREF="http://ericir.syr.edu/">http://ericir.syr.edu/</A>.<BR>
Anyone involved with education can also send an email to AskERIC at <A HREF="mailto:askeric@ericir.syr.edu">askeric@ericir.syr.edu</A>
<P>
