<CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2><FONT SIZE=+3>M</FONT>athkit for <FONT SIZE=+3>T</FONT>oolbook</FONT> </STRONG> </CENTER>
<BR>

<H3>What is MathKit?</H3>
<P>MathKit is a mathematical software construction set that extends ToolBook.  For example, MathKit:
<UL>
<LI>Includes a comprehensive set of mathematical objects and functions that is seamlessly integrated into the ToolBook environment.
<LI>Provides symbolic and numeric computation, statistical data manipulation, near-typeset quality formula display, sophisticated display objects for 2D and 3D graphing with integrated animation.
<LI>Includes a full LOGO implementation for geometric explorations.
<LI>Allows users to do mathematics by using an English-like scripting language, MathScript, eliminating the need for learning a complicated formal programming language.
<LI>Allows its objects to be customized by the author by setting the MathKit object's properties. 
<LI>Contains special DataWindows for data analysis.
</UL>

<P>MathKit for ToolBook will be distributed in the following ways:
<UL>
<LI>Licensed to application developers.
<LI>Provided as a tool to content developers participating in the development of interactive mathematics curriculum materials coordinated by the IAT and funded by Foundations, etc.
<LI>Included as part of custom content development undertaken by the IAT for other parties. </UL>

<P>The IAT has no plans at this time to release an end-user retail version of MathKit for ToolBook.<P>

<HR>
<H3>For Additional Information on MathKit</H3>
<P><B>Contact the Institute for Academic Technology</B>
<BR>Phone:  919-405-1927
<BR>Email:  <A HREF="mailto:mathkit@unc.edu">mathkit@unc.edu</A>
<P>Aspiring authors should check out the <A HREF="http://ike.engr.washington.edu/mathwright/">Mathwright Library</A> - [Mathwright is an example of an authoring system that uses MathKit as its mathematics engine.]   
<P>Or subscribe to the MathKit Discussion List at <A HREF="mail
to:mathkit-request@thoth.stetson.edu">mathkit-request@thoth.stetson.edu</A><P>

