<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="55%">

<DL>
<DT><STRONG>VRML and Drama Studies</STRONG> <IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0></DT>
<DD>A <A HREF="http://www.unc.edu/~chadk/wildduck.wrl">prototype</A>  for the teaching of literature using VRML.  Feel free to explore this VRML representation of the stage of Ibsen's <EM>The Wild 
Duck</EM>.

<P>
<DT><STRONG>VRML 2.0 Specs Available!</STRONG><IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/New.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=13 BORDER=0>
<DD>The specification for <A HREF="http://vag.vrml.org/VRML2.0/FINAL/">VRML 2.0</A> is now online at the VAG's homepages.

<P>
<DT><STRONG>VRML 2.0 Browsers Available</STRONG><IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/New.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=13 BORDER=0>
<DD>Three new browsers are on the market:  Dimension X's <A HREF="http://www.dimensionx.com/products/lr/">Liquid Reality VRML Toolkit</A>,  SGI's <A HREF="http://vrml.sgi.com/">Cosmo Player</A> for Windows95, and Sony's <A HREF="http://vs.sony.co.jp/VS-E/vstop.html">Cyber Passage</A> browser.

<P>
<DT><STRONG>The VRML Repository Gets New Look</STRONG><IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/New.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=13 BORDER=0>
<DD>The VRML Repository's <A HREF="http://www.sdsc.edu/vrml/">web site</A> has been redesigned with an easier interface and the same slick organization.

<P>
<DT><STRONG>New VRML Clearing House</STRONG> <IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0>
<DD><a href="http://www.aereal.com">Aereal Inc.</a>, with their own <a href="http://www.aereal.com/home.wrl.gz">home world</a> (gzipped) comes online with a vast array of links and VRML services, including the <a href="http://www.aereal.com/instant/">instant VRML home world</a> option off their front page.  They also offer links to more than <A HREF="http://www.aereal.com/boom/"> 1000 VRML URLs</A> (yes, seeing is believing).  Overall, this site rivals the Repository as a central clearing house for links to VRML worlds. 

<P>
<DT><STRONG>CyberGate: Alternative VRML</STRONG>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.blacksun.com">Black Sun Interactive </A> announces third beta of its CyberGate Browser, "the browser that turns VRML worlds into multiuser communities."</CENTER>

<P>
<DT><STRONG>Keeping Up with the Bleeding Edge of VRML</STRONG>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.zdnet.com/~zdi/vrml">Ziff-Davis 
Publishing</A> teams up with Black Sun to extend the functionality of its <A HREF=http://www.zdnet.com/zdi/vrml/content/vrmlsite/outside.wrl>Terminal Reality</A>  VRML site.

</TD>

<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/1X17pix.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="17" HEIGHT="600">

<P>"The<FONT SIZE=+1> V</FONT>irtual <FONT SIZE=+1>R</FONT>eality <FONT SIZE=+1>M</FONT>odeling <FONT SIZE=+1>L</FONT>anguage (VRML) is a language for describing ... virtual worlds networked via the global Internet and hyperlinked with the World Wide Web." -- From the Introduction to the <A HREF="http://vrml.wired.com/vrml.tech/vrml10-3.html">VRML Spec 1.0</A> HTML document.

<UL>
<LI><STRONG><A HREF="http://notes.iat.unc.edu:1965/vrml.nsf?OpenDatabase">Discussion Area</A> <IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/New.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=13 BORDER=0></STRONG>

