<TITLE>Java/HotJava: Readings and Resources</TITLE>
<!-- Created: September 27, 1995 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Last revised: December 9, 1996 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Filename = irg-42.html -->
<!-- Former filename = hotjava.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Java/HotJava<FONT SIZE="-1">&#153;</FONT><BR>
Readings and Resources</FONT></STRONG>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised:  November 8, 1996
</CENTER>
<P>
What are Java and HotJava? "Java is a programming language developed by Sun Microsystems that brings animation and interaction to the World Wide Web. HotJava is the name of the software developed by Sun which you can use to observe and interact with Java programs. Java unleashes a level of interactivity that has never been possible on the Web."<BR>
	(From the introduction to <EM><A HREF="http://www.december.com/works/java/intro.html">Presenting Java</A></EM>, by John December.)
<BR><BR><BR>
<A HREF="#articles">Articles/PapersBibliographies</A><BR>
<A HREF="#books">Book Lists and Online Books</A><BR>
<A HREF="#www">WWW Resources</A><BR>
<A HREF="#tools">Tools</A><BR>
<A HREF="#seminars">Online Seminars</A><BR>
<A HREF="#journals">Magazines/Newsletters</A> <BR>
<A HREF="#conferences">Conferences </A>
