<HEAD>
<TITLE>Multimedia Technology: Bibliography</TITLE>
<!-- Corrected: August 17, 1995 -->
<!-- Last revised: February 7, 1997 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Filename = irg-12.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Multimedia Technology: Bibliography</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: February 7, 1997
</CENTER>
<P>
When this resource guide was first compiled, multimedia technology was an emerging field, and it was possible to compile a fairly comprehensive list of the few available sources of general information of interest to educators. This edition of the bibliography contains citations for many of those early books, along with recently-published works. However, it reflects only a part of the vast amount of multimedia books currently in print. More periodical materials have also appeared on the scene, and are reflected in the expanded magazines and journals section. Whole conferences are now devoted to multimedia interests, and a section devoted to these has been added, along with links to a list of multimedia associations.
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="#books">Books</A><BR>
<A HREF="#articles">Articles</A><BR>
<A HREF="#journals">Magazines/Journals</A><BR>
<A HREF="#conferences">Conferences</A><BR>
<A HREF="#associations">Multimedia Associations</A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="books"><STRONG>Books</STRONG></A>
<P>
 Agnew, Palmer W., Anne S. Kellerman, and Jeanine M. Meyer. <EM>Multimedia in 	the Classroom</EM>. Boston: Allyn and Bacon, 1996.
<P>
Ambron, Sueann, and Kristina Hooper. <EM>Learning with Interactive
	Multimedia; Developing and Using Multimedia Tools in Education</EM>.
	Redmond, WA: Microsoft Press, 1990.
<P>
Amron, Sueann, and Kristina Hooper. <EM>Interactive Multimedia; Visions of
	Multimedia for Developers, Educators, and Information
	Providers</EM>. Redmond, WA: Microsoft Press, 1988.
<P>
Aston, Robert, and Joyce Schwarz, eds. <EM>Multimedia: Gateway to the Next
	Millennium</EM>. Boston: AP Professional, 1994.
<P>
 Barron, Ann E., and Gary W. Orwig. <EM>Multimedia Technologies for Training: An 	Introduction</EM>. Englewood, CO: Libraries Unlimited, 1995.
<P>
Brand, Stewart. <EM>The Media Lab</EM>. New York: Viking Penguin, Inc., 1987.
<P>
Burger, Jeff.<EM> The Desktop Multimedia Bible</EM>. Reading, MA: Addison-	Wesley Pub. Co., 1992.
<P>
Dean, Damon A. <EM>A Pocket Tour of Multimedia on the Internet</EM>. San 	Francisco: SYBEX, 1996.
<P>
Desmarais, Norman. <EM>Multimedia on the PC: A Guide for Information
	Professionals</EM>. Westport, CT: Meckler, 1993.
<P>
 Dillon, Patrick M., and David C. Leonard. <EM>Multimedia Technology from A to 	Z</EM>. Phoenix, AZ: Oryx Press, 1995
<P>
Druin, Allison, and Cynthia Solomon. <EM>Designing Multimedia Environments for 	Children</EM>. New York: J. Wiley & Sons, 1996.
<P>
Earnshaw, Rae, and John Vince, eds. <EM>The Internet in 3D: Information, Images, 	and Interaction</EM>. San Diego: Academic Press, 1997.
<P>
Falk, Dennis R., and Helen L. Carlson. <EM>Multimedia in Higher Education: A 	Practical Guide to New Tools for Interactive Teaching and Learning</EM>. 	Medford, NJ: Learned Information, Inc., 1995.
<P>
Floyd, Steve. <EM>The IBM Multimedia Handbook</EM>. New York: Brady 	Publishing, 1991.
<P>
Gayeski, Diane M., ed. <EM>Multimedia for Learning: Development, Application, 	Evaluation</EM>. Englewood, NJ: Educational Technology Publications, 1993.
<P>
Greenberger, Martin, ed. <EM>Technologies for the 21st Century: On
	Multimedia</EM>. Santa Monica, CA: The Voyager Co., 1990.
<P>
Haynes, George R. <EM>Opening Minds: The Evolution of Videodiscs and
	Interactive Learning</EM>. Dubuque, IA: Kendall/Hunt Pub. Co., 1989.
<P>
Hodges, Matthew E., and Russell M. Sasnett, eds. <EM>Multimedia Computing:
	Case Studies from MIT Project Athena</EM>. Reading, MA:
	Addison-Wesley, 1992.
<P>
Hofstetter, Fred T. <EM>Multimedia Literacy</EM>. New York: McGraw-Hill, 1997.
<P>
Iuppa, Nicholas V., and Karl Anderson. <EM>Advanced Interactive Video
	Design: New Techniques and Applications</EM>. White Plains, NY:
	Knowledge Industry Publications, Inc., 1988.
<P>
Keyes, Jessica, ed.<EM> The McGraw-Hill Multimedia Handbook</EM>. New York:
	McGraw-Hill, 1994.
<P>
Koegel Buford, John F., ed.<EM> Multimedia Systems</EM>. New York: ACM 	Press, 1994.
<P>
McIntosh, Stephen. <EM>The Multimedia Producer's Legal Survival Guide</EM>.
	Santa Clara, CA: Multimedia Computing Corp., 1990.
<P>
 Reynolds, Angus, and Thomas Iwinski. <EM>Multimedia Training: Developing 	Technology-based Systems</EM>. New York: McGraw-Hill, 1996.
<P>
<EM>Multimedia and Related Technologies: A Glossary of Terms</EM>. Falls 	Church, VA: Monitor Information Services, 1991.
<P>
Oettinger, Anthony G. <EM>Telling Ripe from Hype in Multimedia: The Ecstasy and 	the Agony</EM>. Cambridge, MA: Program on Information Resources Policy, 	Harvard University, Center for Information Policy Research, 1994.
<P>
Olsen, Gary J. <EM>Getting Started in Multimedia Design</EM>. Cincinnati: North 	Light Books, 1997.
<P>
Perlmutter, Martin. <EM>Producer's Guide to Interactive Videodiscs</EM>. White
	Plains, NY: Knowledge Industry Publications, Inc., 1991.
	<P>
Pinheiro, Edwin J. <EM>Introduction to Multimedia: Featuring Windows 	Applications</EM>. Belmont, CA: Wadsworth Pub. Co., 1996.
<P>
<EM>The Power of Multimedia: A Guide to Interactive Technology in Education
	and Business</EM>. Washington: The Interactive Video Industry
	Association, 1990.
<P>
Rathbone, Andy. <EM>Multimedia & CD-ROMs for Dummies</EM>. 2nd ed. Foster 	City, CA: IDG Books Worldwide, 1995.
<P>
Rosch, Winn L. <EM>Multimedia Bible</EM>. Indianapolis, IN: Sams Pub., 1995.
<P>
Schwier, Richard A., and Earl R. Misanchuk. <EM>Interactive Multimedia
	Instruction</EM>. Englewood Cliffs, NJ: Educational Technology
	Publications, 1993.
<P>
Sneed, Laurel. <EM>Evaluating Video Programs: Is It Worth It?</EM> White Plains,
	NY: Knowledge Industry Publications, Inc., 1991.
<P>
Thomson Technology Services Group. <EM>Multimedia in Education</EM>. 	Belmont, CA: Integrated Media Group, Wadsworth Pub. Co., 1996.
<P>
Tway, Linda. <EM>Multimedia in Action!</EM> Boston: AP Professional, 1995.
<P>
Van Nostran, William. <EM>The Scriptwriter's Handbook: New Techniques for
	Media Writers</EM>. White Plains, NY: Knowledge Industry
	Publications, Inc., 1989.
<P>
Vaughan, Tay. <EM>Multimedia: Making It Work</EM>. 2nd ed. Berkeley: Osborne 	McGraw-Hill, 1994.
<P>
Villamil-Casanova, John, and Louis Molina.  <EM>An Interactive Guide to 	Multimedia</EM>. Indianapolis, IN: Que E&T, 1996.
<P>
Waterworth, John A. <EM>Multimedia Interaction with Computers: Human Factors 	Issues</EM>. New York: Ellis Harwood, 1992.
<P>
Waterworth, John A., ed. <EM>Multimedia: Technology and Applications</EM>. New
	York: Ellis Horwood, 1990.
<P>
Wells, Michael. <EM>Desktop Video</EM>. White Plains, NY: Knowledge Industry
	Publications, Inc., 1989.
<P>
<EM>Who's Who in Interactive Multimedia</EM>. Washington, DC: The Interactive
	Video Industry Association, 1990.
<P>
 Wodaski, Ron. <EM>Multimedia Madness</EM>. 2nd ed. Indianapolis, IN: Sams Pub., 1994
<BR>
