<HR>
<CENTER><H2>"Exploring the World of Computer Networks"</H2>
<P><B>Original Broadcast Date:</B> Thursday, September 30, 1993
<BR>[<A HREF="#overview">Overview</A> | <A HREF="#speakers">Key Speakers</A> | <A HREF="#materials">Supplemental Materials</A> | <A HREF="#video">Video Ordering Information</A>]</CENTER>
<P><HR><P>

<H3><A NAME="overview">Overview</A></H3>

<P>Explore the use of computer networks and sample the vast array of resources available via the Internet, the global educational and research network. In this video, you will hear from a number of experts in computer networking as they explore:
<UL><LI>How to enhance teaching, learning and researching with computer networks.
<LI>How to take advantage of the vast resources available via the Internet.
<LI>The future of the Internet.
<LI>The future of the National Information Infrastructure.
<LI>How to access IAT resources through the Internet.</UL>
<P>Plus, you'll learn more about network, communication and navigation tools such as e-mail, FTP (file transfer protocol), Telnet, CWIS (campus-wide information system), WAIS (wide area information server), Gopher and more.

<H3><A NAME="speakers">Key Speakers</A></H3> 

<UL>
<LI>Jim Gogan - Director of the Office of Information Technology/Networking Systems, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
<LI><A HREF="../../graves/graves.html">William H. Graves</A> - Director of the IAT and Associate Provost for Information Technology, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
<LI>Steve Griffin - IAT Director of Technical Services.
<LI>Carolyn Kotlas - IAT Information Resources Manager.
<LI>Diana G. Oblinger - Academic Programs Manager, IBM Higher Education.
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="materials">Supplemental Materials</A></H3>


<H3><A NAME="video">Video Ordering Information</A></H3>
<UL><LI><A HREF="../vidorder.html">TO ORDER</A>
<LI><A HREF="../resource.html">Information about other videos in the IAT collection</A>
</UL>

