<HR>
<CENTER><H2>"Creating a Campus Network Infrastructure"</H2>
<P><B>Original Broadcast Date:</B> Thursday, March 24, 1994
<BR>[<A HREF="#overview">Overview</A> | <A HREF="#speakers">Key Speakers</A> | <A HREF="#materials">Supplemental Materials</A> | <A HREF="#video">Video Ordering Information</A>]</CENTER>
<P><HR><P>

<H3><A NAME="overview">Overview</A></H3>

<P>What does it take to operate an information technology network on your campus? Whether you're starting from scratch or linking existing networks, this video will show you some of the best ways to plan, install, maintain and upgrade a campus network infrastructure. You will discover how to:

<UL><LI>Identify organizational activities that could benefit from the use of networks.
<LI>Design an infrastructure that will work with the widest range of technologies.
<LI>Select appropriate wiring and connectors.
<LI>Identify the tools and competencies required to maintain the network.
<LI>Choose appropriate management tools and practices.
<LI>Fund your network today and tomorrow.</UL>

<P>You'll learn by example. Throughout the video, our program leaders develop a representative information technology infrastructure, stepping you through logical design, topology, physical media, installation, maintenance, personnel management and more.

<H3><A NAME="speakers">Key Speakers</A></H3> 

<UL>
<LI>Jim Gogan - Director of the Office of Information Technology/Networking Systems, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
<LI>Steve Griffin - IAT Director of Technical Services.
<LI>David R. Luttrell - IAT Manager of Network Integration Services.
<LI>Thomas Toher - Senior Information Developer, IBM Networking Systems.
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="materials">Supplemental Materials</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="../../../guides/irg-15.html">Creating a Campus Network Infrastructure: Bibliography</A>
 
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="video">Video Ordering Information</A></H3>
<UL><LI><A HREF="../vidorder.html">TO ORDER</A>
<LI><A HREF="../resource.html">Information about other videos in the IAT collection</A>
</UL>

<P>
