<PRE>	

</PRE>
<CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2><FONT SIZE=+3>S</FONT>atellite <FONT SIZE=+3>B</FONT>roadcast <FONT SIZE=+3>V</FONT>ideotapes </FONT> </STRONG> </CENTER>
<BR>

<H3>NEW!</H3>

<P><A HREF="archive/may96.html">"Mapping the Future: New Routes to Learning Productivity"</A> - The IAT's May broadcast video will be available by the end of June. In this video our panel of experts discuss critical issues encountered by Educom's National Learning Infrastructure Initiative during the past year and explore some of their new and exciting prototype projects, including: Virginia Polytechnic Institute and State University's "Cyberschool" concept; Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute's "studio" approach to college physics and calculus courses; and the Education Network of Maine's statewide distance education system. 
<BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: May 1996)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]


<P><A HREF="archive/march96.html">"From Reality to Virtuality: New Tools for Distributed Learning"</A> - In this broadcast, virtual reality pioneers discussed and explored worlds they have created and assessed virtual reality as a means for creating dynamic and engaging learning environments. A range of technology levels were covered - from the use of VRML to design desktop virtual environments for the Web, to the use of peripheral technologies to create fully immersive learning environments. <BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: March 1996)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]

<P><HR>
<H3>Previous Broadcasts</H3>
<P><A HREF="archive/feb93.html">Multimedia: How Does It Really Work In the Classroom?</A> - An introduction to multimedias ability to enhance teaching and learning. <BR><I>Price: $50. (Broadcast date: February 1993)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/sept93.html">Exploring the World of Computer Networks</A> - Explore the uses of computer networks and sample the vast array of resources available via the Internet, the global educational and research network. <BR><I>Price: $195. (Broadcast date: September 1993)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/dec93.html">Technology Across the Campus: Creating a Student-Centered Environment</A> - Find out how information technology can create a student-centered environment on your campus. <BR><I>Price: $195. (Broadcast date: December 1993)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/feb94.html">Classroom Design With Technology In Mind</A> - Discover the art of creating classrooms that match technological form with pedagogical function. <BR><I>Price: $195. (Broadcast date: February 1994)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/march94.html">Creating a Campus Network Infrastructure</A> - Learn about the physical and support issues involved in planning, installing, maintaining and upgrading a campus network infrastructure. <BR><I>Price: $195. (Broadcast date: March 1994)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/april94.html">Moving Toward a National Learning Infrastructure</A> - Examine national efforts to emphasize the role of information technology in increasing access and adding value to higher education. <BR><I>Price: $195. (Broadcast date: April 1994)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]<P>
<HR>
<H3>Fall 1994 Series: Broadcast Videotapes</H3>
<P><A HREF="archive/sept94.html">Reengineering Distributed Learning Environments</A> - Examine ways to apply process reengineering to the design of learning environments, from hardware and software to facility design and learning theory. <BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: September 1994)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/oct94.html">Instructional Technology Review and Update</A> - Includes discussion and technical demonstrations of instructional technology from the basics to the cutting edge. <BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: October 1994)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/dec94.html">Libraries: Todays Issues, Tomorrows Challenges</A> - Discover the potential impact and solutions to several issues confronting library professionals. <BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: December 1994)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P>
<HR>
<H3>Spring 1995 Series: Broadcast Videotapes</H3>
<P><A HREF="archive/feb95.html">Hi-Touch Technology: Authenticity in the Learning Environment</A> - Discover how to implement and integrate technology throughout the entire spectrum of instruction. <BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: February 1995)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/march95.html">Distributed Learning Environments: An Integrating Model for Distance Education</A> - Includes discussion of institutional and pedagogical perspectives on the need for customized learning environments and the technologies that help us create them. <BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: March 1995)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><A HREF="archive/april95.html">Higher Education/K-12 Connection: Using Technology to Assist Public Schools</A> - Explore the possibilities of collaboration between public schools, higher education, federal and state governments and the private sector. <BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: April 1995)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]
<P><HR>
<P><A HREF="archive/novem95.html">"Computer Conferencing: Alternative to Lectures"</A> - See demonstrations of computer conferencing in a wide range of courses and with diverse student populations, and examine the benefits of computer conferencing from both the teacher's and learner's points of view, with emphasis on issues such as motivation, student interaction, empowerment, and depth and understanding of subject matter through dialogue. <BR><I>Price: $295. (Broadcast date: November 1995)</I> [<A HREF="vidorder.html"> To Order</A> ]

<P>

