</TABLE>


<PRE>	

</PRE>
<CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2><FONT SIZE=+3>E</FONT>mail <FONT SIZE=+3>L</FONT>ists</FONT> </STRONG> </CENTER>
<BR>

<P>In addition to our Web site, the IAT has a selection of electronic lists designed to bring you timely information and interactive options for communication.  

<P>To subscribe to any of these listservers, click on the list name and type in the message:  
<P>
<DD><KBD>subscribe &#40;listname&#41; your_name</KBD> 

<DD>Example: <KBD> subscribe IATNEWS Sigmund Freud</KBD>

<P> Then send the mail. Remember to leave the subject line blank.

<P>If you are using a text-only browser, send the same message to listserv@unc.edu.

<UL>
<LI><STRONG><A HREF="mailto:listserv@unc.edu">IATNEWS</A></STRONG> - A one-way-only list that provides you with periodic news releases regarding the IAT -- from event listings to articles on IAT successes and new developments -- the same information you are used to getting from Briefings.  * Note * PUBS-IAT subscribers have been added automatically.

<P>
<LI><STRONG><A HREF="mailto:listserv@unc.edu">INFOBITS</A></STRONG> - IAT Information Resources Groups monthly electronic newsletter that provides short articles related to instruction and information technology world wide.

<P>
<LI><STRONG><A HREF="mailto:listserv@unc.edu">IATFORUM</A></STRONG> - An open discussion list on issues involving technology and education, including IAT workshops and satellite broadcasts and topics important to educators in the information age.

<P>
<LI><STRONG><A HREF="mailto:listserv@unc.edu">WEBAPP</A></STRONG> - A user support forum for <A HREF="../software/webapp/index.html">WebApp</A>, an IAT software utility that simplifies installing and running software distributed via World Wide Web.         

<P>
<LI><STRONG><A HREF="mailto:listserv@unc.edu">IATXA</A></STRONG> - A user support forum for <A HREF="../software/express/express.html">Express Author</A>, IAT software for quick and easy multimedia development with Asymetrix ToolBook.  

</UL>

