<H1>William H. Graves, Ph.D.</H1>
<H2>Founder
<BR>Institute for Academic Technology</H2>
<HR>
<P><B>Dr. Graves</B>, in addition to being the Founder of the IAT, is Chief Information Officer (Interim) and Professor of Mathematics at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.  A national leader in the educational use of information technology, he continues to help coordinate the IAT's effort to integrate academic and industry concerns.
<H3>Papers</H3>
<P>The following is a list of papers written by Dr. Graves that are currently available on the IAT's Web site.  Please click on any title to view the paper.
<P>
<UL>
<P><LI>Graves, William H. <A HREF="graves4.txt">"The Educational Ecosystem of Information and Computation: Medium and Message."</A> <I>EDUCOM Review</I>, vol. 28, no. 5 (September/October 1993).
<P>
<LI>Graves, William H. <A HREF="graves9.html">"Higher Education and the NII - From Vision to Reality."</A> This paper is adapted from the author's article which appeared in "Higher Education and the NII: From Vision to Reality," Monterey Conference Proceedings, September 1995, published by EDUCOM. 
<P>
<P><LI>Graves, William H. <A HREF="graves10.html">"A Higher Education Perspective on Network Applications."</A> This paper is adapted from the author's article which appeared in "Higher Education and the NII: From Vision to Reality," Monterey Conference Proceedings, September 1995, published by EDUCOM.
