<HEAD>
<TITLE>James S. Noblitt</TITLE>
<!-- Last revised: July 29, 1996 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Filename = noblitt.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/noblitt.gif" ALIGN=left HSPACE=10>
<H1>James S. Noblitt, Ph.D.</H1>
<H2>Academic Chair
<BR>Institute for Academic Technology</H2>
<HR>
<P><B>Dr. Noblitt</B>, in addition to being Academic Chair of the IAT, is Research Professor of Romance Languages at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.  
Dr. Noblitt received a BA and an MA degree in French literature from the University of Virginia, and a PhD in French linguistics at Harvard. He has worked as a research linguist at the Center for Applied Linguistics in Washington, D.C., as a professor of linguistics at Cornell University and as an IBM Consulting Scholar. His research interests at the IAT include the use of multimedia for instruction and the role of information technology in research and learning. Dr. Noblitt is co-author of a program for writing assistance in French, <I>Syst&#232;me-D</I>, winner of the 1988 EDUCOM/NCRIPTAL award for Best Foreign Language Software. He has recently published <I><A HREF="../../technology/demos/nouvelle.html">Nouvelles Dimensions</A></I>, a multimedia program for listening comprehension in French that was named Grand Prize Winner at the 1995 Asymetrix Developers Conference.  

<H3>Papers</H3>
<P>The following is a list of papers written by Dr. Noblitt that are currently available on the IAT's Web site.  Please click on any title to view the paper.
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Noblitt, James S. <A HREF="noblitt3.html">"Cognitive Approaches to Listening Comprehension."</A> In <EM>Selected Proceedings of the 1995 Joint
Conference of the Southern Conference on Language Teaching and the South Carolina Foreign Language Teachers' Association.</EM> Valdosta, GA: Valdosta State University, 1995.
</UL>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Noblitt, James S. <A HREF="noblitt1.html">"Enhancing Instruction with Multimedia."</A> In <EM>Selected Papers from the Fourth National Conference on College Teaching and Learning.</EM> Jacksonville, FL: Florida Community College, 1995.<BR>
This article has also been reprinted in <EM>Syllabus</EM> 8, no. 9 (June 1995): 28.
</UL>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Noblitt, James S. <A HREF="noblitt2.html">"Scholarship, Publishing and Computing: Interactions in the Educational Marketplace."</A> <EM>IAT Briefings</EM> (1995).
</UL>
