<HEAD>
<TITLE>EPSS: Readings and Resources</TITLE>
<! -- Created: September 20, 1996 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<! -- Last revised: January 16, 1997 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<! -- Filename = irg-47.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Electronic Performance Support Systems: Readings and Resources</FONT></STRONG>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: January 16, 1997</CENTER>
<P>	
What is an Electronic Performance Support System? "Basically, an EPSS is an integrated, computer-based environment that provides workers immediate access to a full range of information, tools, and training -- often
right on the same automated information system where workers do their job. The purpose of the EPSS is to improve job performance with immediately accessible support:  When it is needed.  At the place it is needed. In the amount it is needed. In the form it is needed." <BR>
-- The Mitre Corporation
<P>
<A HREF="#articles">Articles/Papers/Books</A><BR>
<A HREF="#www">WWW Resources</A><BR>
<A HREF="#examples">EPSS Examples</A><BR>
<A HREF="#magazines">Magazines/Newsletters</A> <BR>
<A HREF="#associations">Associations</A><BR>
<A HREF="#conferences">Conferences</A> <BR>
<BR><BR><BR>
<A NAME="articles"><STRONG>Articles/Papers/Books</STRONG></A>
<P>
Brown, Lesley A. <EM>Designing and Developing Electronic Performance Support Systems</EM>. Boston: Digital Press, 1996.
<P>
