<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Assessments of Multimedia Technology in Education: Bibliography</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: December 4, 1996
</CENTER>
<P>
Is there any evidence that multimedia technology is more effective for delivering instruction than traditional methods? Is there more than anecdotal evidence to show that the educational results justify the cost and effort of incorporating multimedia technology into the classroom? To help answer these questions, we have a growing body of research devoted to assessing the effectiveness of multimedia in all levels of education, including corporate and military training.
<BR><BR><BR>
Adam, Gregory L. "Why Interactive?" <EM>Multimedia & Videodisc Monitor</EM> 10
	(March 1992): 20.
<P>
Alifrangis, Catherine. "An Integrated Learning System in an Elementary
	School: Implementation, Attitudes, and Results." Paper
	presented at the 7th International Conference on Technology and
	Education, Brussels, Belgium, March 20-22, 1990.
<P>
Barron, Ann. "A CD-ROM Tutorial: Training for a New Technology."
	<EM>Educational Technology</EM> 30 (June 1990): 20-23.
<P>
Barron, Ann, and M. L. Kysilka. "The Effectiveness of Digital Audio in
	Computer-Based Training." <EM>Journal of Research on Computing in
	Education</EM> 25, no. 3 (1993): 277-289.
<P>
Berman, Judith et al. "Feasibility of Incorporating Alternative
	Teaching Methods into Clinical Clerkships." <EM>Teaching and
	Learning in Medicine</EM> 2, no. 2 (1990): 98-103.
<P>
Bingham, M. H. "Results of Two Studies on the Benefits and Pitfalls of
	Technology-Based Information Accessing." <EM>T.H.E. Journal</EM> 20, no.
	4 (1992): 88-92.
<P>
Block, S. H. "Applying Technology to Workforce Training." <EM>Interactive
	Learning International</EM> 8, no. 4 (1992): 311-14.
<P>
Bolton, J. P. R. et al. "The Water Videodisc: A Problem-Solving
	Environment." <EM>Computers and Education</EM> 15, no. 1-3 (1990):
	165-72.
<P>
Borras, Isabel. "Developing and Assessing Practicing Spoken French: A
	Multimedia Program for Improving Speaking Skills."<EM> Educational
	Technology Research and Development</EM> 41, no. 4 (1993): 91-103.
<P>
Bosco, James. "An Analysis of Evaluations of Interactive Video." <EM>Educational 	Technology</EM> 26,  no. 5 (May 1986): 7-17.
<P>
Bosco, James. "An Analysis of Evaluations of Interactive Video." Paper
	presented at the 5th International Conference on Computers and
	Education, Brussels, Belgium, March 20-22, 1990.
<P>
