<A NAME="7"><STRONG>U. S. Copyright Office</STRONG></A>
<P>
U.S. Copyright Office. "Copyright Basics." Washington, DC: Library of Congress, 1992.<BR>
Available online: <A HREF="http://lcweb.loc.gov/copyright/circs/circ01.html">http://lcweb.loc.gov/copyright/circs/circ01.html</A>
<P>
U.S. Copyright Office contact information<BR>
<UL>
<LI>By mail: Copyright Office, Library of Congress, Washington, D.C. 20559-6000.<BR> 
<LI>By telephone:<BR>
&#183; 202-707-3000 -- to speak to a Copyright Information Specialist or get information on forms and publications<BR>
Available between 8:30 a.m.-5:00 p.m., Eastern Time, Monday-Friday, except Federal Holidays. After hours, prerecorded information messages are available at this number.<BR>
&#183; 202-707-9100 -- to order Copyright Office publications or application forms (caller must know which titles to request). Available 24 hours a day.
<LI>By fax:<BR>
202-707-2600 for fax-on-demand documents
<LI>On the Web:<BR>
<A HREF="http://lcweb.loc.gov/copyright/">http://lcweb.loc.gov/copyright/</A>
<LI>By gopher:<BR>
<A HREF="gopher://marvel.loc.gov:70/11/copyright">gopher://marvel.loc.gov:70/11/copyright</A>
</UL>
