<TITLE>Online Resources for the Solo Librarian</TITLE>
<!-- Created September 19, 1996 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Last revised: January 22, 1997 -->
<!-- Filename = irg-44.html -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Online Resources for the Solo Librarian</FONT></STRONG><BR>
<P>Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS <BR>
Institute for Academic Technology <BR>
Last revised: January 22, 1997</CENTER>
<P>
A collection of handy links for information professionals working in isolated or specialized libraries, or in other settings with limited access to a wide variety of on-site reference resources and other tools of the library profession.
<P>
<STRONG>
<A HREF="#1">Useful Tools and Services</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="#2">Book Information and Reviews</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="#3">Reference Desks and Virtual Libraries</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="#4">Professional Reading</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="#5">Professional Organizations</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="#6">Librarian's Marketplace</A>
</STRONG>
<BR><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><STRONG><A NAME="1">Useful Tools and Services</A></STRONG></FONT>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="telnet://locis.loc.gov">Library of Congress Catalogs</A> <BR>
Can be a source for copy cataloging information for small libraries without OCLC access. Site also includes a LOC subject headings database.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="telnet://dra.com">Digital Research Associates, Inc. (DRA) Online Catalog</A><BR>
Contains much of LOC's cataloging information, but the user interface is much easier to use. This is my preferred source for quick verification of a book citation, ISBN, or call number.
<P>
<LI><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="NEW"> <A HREF="http://library.usask.ca/hywebcat/">webCATS</A><BR>
A directory to library catalogs on the World Wide Web, this is the next generation of Hytelnet. Also includes links to library vendors' Web sites.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.dialog.com/">Knight-Ridder / DIALOG</A><BR>
Includes online copies of DIALOG Blue Sheets.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://sunsite.berkeley.edu/">Berkeley Digital Library SunSITE</A><BR>
 Excellent source of information and tools for librarians buiding digital collections.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.metronet.lib.mn.us/lc/lc1.html">Libcat: A Guide to Library Resources on the Internet</A><BR>
Includes useful tips on locating special collections
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/athens/8459/lc.html">Library of Congress Classification System</A><BR>
A browsable listing of LC System call number ranges. As a work in progress, the ranges are continually being expanded.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.oclc.org/">OCLC</A><BR>
Includes demonstrations and research papers.
<P>

</UL>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><STRONG><A NAME="2">Book Information and Reviews</A></STRONG></FONT>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.amazon.com/">Amazon.com Bookstore</A><BR>
Extensive booklist plus many reviews of what they sell.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ambook.org/">American Booksellers Association BookWeb</A><BR>
News and information about books and the bookselling industry. Includes a searchable database of bookstores.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ala.org/booklist/">Booklist</A><BR>
American Library Association's <EM>Booklist</EM> magazine
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.reedref.com/boop.html">Books Out-Of-Print</A><BR>
Searchable database of out of print books.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cs.cmu.edu/web/books.html">The On-line Books Page</A><BR>
Index of thousands of online books, and directory of common repositories of online books and other documents. 
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.hwwilson.com/retintro.html">Rettig on Reference</A><BR>
Written by James Rettig, the site presents monthly reviews of more than a dozen new adult reference books and several Internet-based reference sources. Items reviewed are selected for their relevance to the North American library community.
<P>
<LI><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT=""> <A HREF="http://www.onzine.com/books.htm">Onzine's On Books</A><BR>
Provides links to the Web pages of large publishing houses and small presses.
<P>
</UL>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><STRONG><A NAME="3">Reference Desks and Virtual Libraries</A></STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Links to a vast variety of online catalogs, reference tools, and information for library professionals.
<P>
<UL>
<LI><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/update.gif" BORDER=0 ALT=""> <A HREF="http://www.bubl.bath.ac.uk/BUBL/home.html">The BUBL Information Service</A>
<P>
<LI><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/update.gif" BORDER=0 ALT=""> <A HREF="http://www.public.iastate.edu/~CYBERSTACKS/homepage.html">CyberStacks</A><BR>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.servtech.com/public/mvail/home.html">Digital Librarian</A>
<P>
<LI><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="NEW"> <A HREF="http://www.dra.com/resources/library/librarianslibrary.htm">Digital Research Associates "Librarian's Library"</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.indiana.edu/~librcsd/resource/ready/">Indiana University Libraries Quick Reference</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.indiana.edu/~librcsd/resource/library/">Indiana University Libraries "Library Resources on the Internet"</A> 
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://sunsite.berkeley.edu/Libweb/">Libweb: Library Servers via WWW</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.library.nwu.edu/resources/library/">Northwestern University Library Networked Resources</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://sjcpl.lib.in.us/homepage/publiclibraries/publiclibraryservers.html">St. Joseph County Public Library's List of Public Libraries with Internet Services</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ex.ac.uk/~ijtilsed/lib/wwwlibs.html">University of Exeter Library and Related Resources</A>
<P>
