<TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>
<H1>What's New? for November 1, 1996</H1>
</CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD>



<A HREF="http://www.learnnc.org/ndex.html"><IMG SRC="http://www.learnnc.org/media/logo-200.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 ALT="LEARN North Carolina Logo" BORDER=0 WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=120></A>
<P><FONT SIZE=4>IAT joins new K-12 initiative: </CENTER><A HREF="http://projects.iat.unc.edu/atwr/index.htm">LEARN  North Carolina</A></FONT>
 (Learners' & Educators' Assistance and Resource Network of North Carolina) is a professional
development and support program for North Carolina teachers and administrators that will help transform K-12
instruction, delivery of instruction, and learning. 
<BR><BR><BR>
<IMG SRC="../media/photos/jimn.jpg" align=left border=o width=180 height=149 HSPACE=10>
<P><CENTER><FONT SIZE=4>IAT Academic Chair wins national award for French language learning programs</FONT></CENTER><BR>
Jim Noblitt, IAT's academic chair and a research professor of romance languages at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, was recently honored as a winner in the 1996 Educom Medal awards program for his promotion of computer-assisted instruction for language learning.
<BR><BR><BR>
<P>Additionally, <STRONG><EM><A HREF="../publications/monitor/monitor.html">The Monitor</A></EM></STRONG>, continues this month with an article titled, "Noblitt Wins Award for French Language Learning Programs." 

<P>
</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>

