<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><STRONG><FONT SIZE=+2>What's What on the Web</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1>Finding New Resources On -- and Information About -- the Internet</FONT></STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: October 30, 1996
</CENTER>
<P>
<H4>Announcements of New Resources</H4>
<A HREF="http://www.drake.edu/Gleason_index.html"><STRONG>Net-Happenings</STRONG></A> -- a service of InterNIC Directory & Database Services and the list moderator, Gleason Sackman of North Dakota's SENDIT Network for K-12 educators
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.mcs.com/~jcr/INSITE.html"><STRONG>In Site</STRONG></A> -- announcements of new Internet sites; Librarian Gary Price's current awareness service for librarians and other information professionals
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<STRONG><A HREF="http://gort.ucsd.edu/newjour/">NewJour</A></STRONG> -- archive of electronic journal and newsletter announcements from the newjour listserv
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://rs.internic.net/scout_report-index.html"><STRONG>The Scout Report</STRONG></A> -- a weekly publication offered by InterNIC Information Services combining new resource announcements and other news which occurred on the Internet during the previous week
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.ci.berkeley.ca.us/bpl/bkmk/new.html"><STRONG>Berkeley Public Library's "What's New This Week"</STRONG></A> -- listing of new sites located by Library staff.
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.hw.ac.uk/libWWW/irn/irn.html"><STRONG>Internet Resources Newsletter</STRONG></A> --  monthly newsletter, edited by Heriot-Watt
University Library staff and published by Heriot-Watt University Internet Resource Centre. Each issue contains short articles on topics of current interest, lists of new Internet resources of interest to the academic community, and especially, but not exclusively, UK resources.
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://home.netscape.com/escapes/whats_new.html"><STRONG>Netscape's What's New</STRONG></A> page -- from the Netscape browser's Web site
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/picks/"><STRONG>Yahoo's Picks of the Week</STRONG></A> -- links to other sites recommended by the Yahoo staff
<P>
<!==========================================================>
 <A HREF="http://www.directory.net/dir/whats-new.html"><STRONG>What's New in Commercial Sites on the Web</STRONG></A> -- Open Market's Commercial Sites Index
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT=""> <STRONG><A HREF="http://newtoo.manifest.com/">What's New Too!</A> </STRONG> --  Manifest Information Services' announcements of new Web sites
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://cool.infi.net/"><STRONG>Cool Site of the Day</STRONG></A> -- not always new sites...but usually a surprise
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.washington.edu/nic-news"><STRONG>NIC-News</STRONG></A> -- The NIC-News newsletter was written between January, 1992 and June, 1995, by Sheryl Erez at the University of Washington's Network Information Center. All issues are available here, including hyperlinks to the resources discussed therein.
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://andromeda.einet.net:80/GJ/"><STRONG>Gopher Jewels</STRONG></A> -- catalogs many of the best Gopher sites by categories<BR>
 [Note: Gopher Jewels listserv ceased publication May 1995.]
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~mengwong/whatsnew.list.html"><STRONG>Meta-List of What's New Pages</STRONG></A> --  limited to new things on the Web only
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<HR>
<H4>Links to Education-Related Internet Resources</H4>
<A HREF="http://www.drake.edu/Gleason_index.html"><STRONG>Net-Happenings</STRONG></A>
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://ole.net/ole/"><STRONG>Online Educator</STRONG></A> -- monthly ideas for teachers and lessons that involve using the global network of computers in your classroom; weekly pointers to new places to visit to make the Internet a useful classroom tool
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://cnet.unb.ca/c-edres/"><STRONG>C-EdRes</STRONG></A> --  Canadian site that finds and evaluates education-related Internet resources<BR>
includes a searchable database, an email list, and an anonymous FTP site
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://cnet.unb.ca/c-arts/"><STRONG>C-Arts Web</STRONG></A> -- Canadian site that links to Internet resources on arts and arts education, including drama, literary arts, music, performance arts, and visual arts
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Education/"><STRONG>Yahoo's list of education sites</STRONG></A>
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<HR>
<H4>Information about the Internet</H4>
<A HREF="http://www.educom.edu/web/edupage.html"><STRONG>EDUPAGE</STRONG></A> --  a summary of news items on information technology provided three times each week as a service by Educom
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.mid.net:80/NEWSLETTER/"><STRONG>Newsltr</STRONG></A> --  a mailing list of newsletters and electronic magazines selected for distribution by     Gleason Sackman; the selection includes newsletters covering educational concerns, computer product information, federal news, and information technology
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/update.gif" BORDER=0 ALT=""> <A HREF="http://www.openmarket.com/intindex/"><STRONG>The Internet Index</STRONG></A> -- an occasional collection of facts and statistics about the Internet and related activities
<P>
<!==========================================================>
<A HREF="http://www.december.com/cmc/info/index.html"><STRONG>Pointers to more information about the Internet than you'll ever have time to read or want to.</STRONG></A>
